WEBVTT

00:01.002 --> 00:04.803
[♪♪♪]

00:11.746 --> 00:13.679
♪ Candles burning low ♪

00:13.714 --> 00:16.749
♪ Lots of mistletoe ♪

00:16.784 --> 00:19.651
♪ Lots of snow and ice ♪

00:19.720 --> 00:22.788
♪ Everywhere we go ♪

00:22.857 --> 00:25.991
♪ Choirs singing Carols ♪

00:26.027 --> 00:27.726
♪ Right outside my door ♪

00:27.795 --> 00:29.595
♪ All these things... ♪

00:29.630 --> 00:31.463
It's called risgrynsgrot...

00:31.499 --> 00:33.799
Which is basically
Christmas rice porridge.

00:33.834 --> 00:35.412
♪ ...that's what Christmas
means to me, my love... ♪

00:35.436 --> 00:36.402
Sounds great.

00:36.437 --> 00:38.670
But the best part?

00:38.706 --> 00:41.840
Based on Swedish
Christmas tradition,

00:41.876 --> 00:43.142
whoever finds

00:43.177 --> 00:44.376
the almond

00:44.445 --> 00:46.278
will be married
within a year.

00:46.313 --> 00:49.281
Thank you.

00:49.316 --> 00:50.916
All right, good luck!

00:50.951 --> 00:53.719
♪ ...even though
I love you madly ♪

00:53.754 --> 00:56.755
♪ It seems I love you more ♪

00:56.824 --> 00:59.958
♪ The little cards
you give me ♪

00:59.994 --> 01:01.493
♪ Will touch my heart
for sure... ♪

01:01.529 --> 01:03.429
[Squealing and laughing]

01:03.464 --> 01:04.730
♪ ...all these things
and more ♪

01:04.765 --> 01:07.533
♪ All these things and more ♪

01:07.568 --> 01:10.269
♪ That's what Christmas
means to me, my love ♪

01:10.337 --> 01:11.837
♪ Christmas
means to me, my love... ♪

01:11.872 --> 01:13.639
I love sharing

01:13.674 --> 01:15.140
all the different
holiday traditions

01:15.176 --> 01:17.810
that I've experienced.

01:17.845 --> 01:19.244
You know,
my editor thinks

01:19.280 --> 01:20.779
that I should write
them all down

01:20.815 --> 01:22.915
and publish them
in a book.

01:22.950 --> 01:24.583
That's a good idea.

01:24.618 --> 01:25.962
You always have the most
interesting stories.

01:25.986 --> 01:27.386
Perk of being
a travel writer.

01:27.421 --> 01:29.621
That and global entry getting me
past the airport lines.

01:31.158 --> 01:32.878
You know, you should look
into getting that.

01:34.328 --> 01:35.328
Yeah...

01:36.263 --> 01:37.763
William...

01:37.798 --> 01:40.432
The, uh... the almond,
and your expression.

01:42.136 --> 01:43.635
We've only been
dating six months.

01:47.141 --> 01:49.575
Listen, my parents called
yesterday,

01:49.610 --> 01:51.543
and they want me in Boston
for Christmas,

01:51.579 --> 01:53.078
and I want to be with them.

01:55.015 --> 01:57.816
It's Christmas, em,

01:57.852 --> 01:58.817
and being with my family

01:58.853 --> 02:00.219
is an important tradition
for me,

02:00.287 --> 02:01.647
and I would love
to have you there.

02:03.190 --> 02:06.892
You know I'm more transient
than traditional.

02:08.294 --> 02:11.029
Yeah, I know.

02:11.065 --> 02:12.965
I mean, people probably
always tell you

02:13.000 --> 02:14.333
that one day
you'll settle down,

02:14.368 --> 02:15.801
but...

02:15.836 --> 02:18.604
I don't know
that you will...

02:18.639 --> 02:21.607
At least,
not with a regular guy like me.

02:23.844 --> 02:24.776
[Em]: So...

02:24.845 --> 02:28.080
We broke up...

02:30.684 --> 02:32.151
Which doesn't seem
to surprise you.

02:32.186 --> 02:34.820
You can't fake
chemistry,

02:34.889 --> 02:35.932
especially when one half
of the couple

02:35.956 --> 02:37.589
is rarely in town.

02:37.625 --> 02:39.703
That's because someone
whom I'm pointing at right now

02:39.727 --> 02:40.904
keeps sending me out
on assignments.

02:40.928 --> 02:42.561
Would you like me to stop?

02:42.596 --> 02:44.696
No.
You know I love it.

02:44.732 --> 02:45.964
I do know that,

02:46.000 --> 02:47.699
though I don't know
how you do it.

02:48.769 --> 02:50.269
Experience.

02:50.304 --> 02:51.681
I grew up
living out of my suitcase.

02:51.705 --> 02:53.438
I guess I'm used to it.

02:53.474 --> 02:56.108
And as your editor,
I love that about you.

02:56.177 --> 02:57.177
As your friend...

02:58.913 --> 02:59.913
Say it.

03:01.448 --> 03:02.814
I want you to get that almond.

03:06.153 --> 03:07.920
That would require me

03:07.955 --> 03:09.354
to stay
in one place

03:09.390 --> 03:11.990
for an extended
period of time.

03:12.026 --> 03:13.336
One day, you're going
to find someone

03:13.360 --> 03:15.494
who'll make you want
to do exactly that.

03:15.529 --> 03:16.995
I did.

03:17.031 --> 03:18.363
Speaking of,

03:18.432 --> 03:20.043
you're welcome to join
Keith and me for Christmas.

03:20.067 --> 03:21.133
The kids'd be
over the moon

03:21.168 --> 03:22.734
to have auntie
Emory there.

03:22.770 --> 03:24.136
Aw, I love them,

03:24.205 --> 03:25.482
but I was thinking
about renting a cabin

03:25.506 --> 03:26.438
up to the mountains

03:26.507 --> 03:27.573
and relaxing

03:27.641 --> 03:30.175
before someone sends me
my next assignment.

03:31.645 --> 03:32.878
You're going
to be alone?

03:32.947 --> 03:34.146
On Christmas?

03:34.181 --> 03:35.514
It's not the first time.

03:35.583 --> 03:37.115
I'll be okay.

03:40.287 --> 03:41.420
[School bell ringing]

03:43.000 --> 03:49.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:50.598 --> 03:52.331
You can't get that
tie off fast enough.

03:52.399 --> 03:53.610
Reminds me
I spent all day in court.

03:53.634 --> 03:54.733
Oh, please.

03:54.768 --> 03:56.046
You spend 90% of
your time in jeans.

03:56.070 --> 03:57.236
One of the perks

03:57.271 --> 03:58.615
of leaving the corporate
counsel world behind.

03:58.639 --> 04:00.739
Oh, maybe I should
give it a try.

04:00.808 --> 04:02.507
So you stay at
a hotel for Christmas?

04:02.543 --> 04:03.642
Uh-huh.

04:03.677 --> 04:06.278
My Nana comes over,
we open up presents,

04:06.313 --> 04:08.647
and then we go to a hotel
for brunch.

04:08.716 --> 04:10.449
What do you
and your mom do?

04:10.517 --> 04:11.783
We go to pine grove.

04:11.852 --> 04:13.163
It's my favorite
place for Christmas,

04:13.187 --> 04:14.720
like, ever.

04:14.755 --> 04:16.488
- Have you ever gone?
- No.

04:16.523 --> 04:18.123
You've got to.

04:18.158 --> 04:20.158
There's sledding,
ice skating,

04:20.194 --> 04:21.303
and we get to chop
down our own tree.

04:21.327 --> 04:22.328
Really?

04:22.396 --> 04:23.895
Yeah, it's so much fun!

04:23.931 --> 04:25.130
Katy!

04:25.199 --> 04:26.932
Dad!

04:27.001 --> 04:28.100
Hi, sweetheart.

04:31.171 --> 04:32.282
Do you have
to go back to work?

04:32.306 --> 04:33.705
Nope,
I'm done for the holidays,

04:33.774 --> 04:35.752
and I figured we could do
some Christmas shopping today.

04:35.776 --> 04:37.276
What are you guys doing
for Christmas?

04:37.311 --> 04:40.579
We'll probably just go
to brunch with my mom.

04:40.614 --> 04:41.947
That sounds fun.

04:42.016 --> 04:43.849
Yeah, it's fun.
Right?

04:44.918 --> 04:45.951
Some year,

04:45.986 --> 04:46.718
you guys should try
and get out

04:46.787 --> 04:48.153
to the mountains.

04:48.188 --> 04:49.599
It really brings out
that Christmas spirit.

04:49.623 --> 04:50.922
Yeah, maybe someday.

04:53.794 --> 04:55.127
All right,
put your hood on.

04:55.195 --> 04:57.062
Let's make a run for it.
You ready?

04:57.097 --> 04:58.930
Set... go!
Come on!

05:21.889 --> 05:23.121
[Editor]:
So...

05:23.157 --> 05:25.590
About your trip to the
cabin in the mountains.

05:25.626 --> 05:28.660
How much relaxation
do you actually need?

05:28.696 --> 05:30.862
Are you about
to give me an assignment

05:30.898 --> 05:32.664
right before
my vacation?

05:32.700 --> 05:33.932
Here's the deal.

05:33.967 --> 05:35.545
Phil Laskert was supposed
to give me an article

05:35.569 --> 05:37.636
to publish online
for Christmas day,

05:37.671 --> 05:39.971
but he apparently is stuck
on an ice floe

05:40.040 --> 05:41.206
in the antarctic.

05:41.241 --> 05:42.341
Again?

05:42.376 --> 05:44.376
[Chuckling]
So I'm in bit of a pickle.

05:44.411 --> 05:45.711
Hey, did I ever tell you

05:45.746 --> 05:48.180
about the German tradition
of the Christmas pickle?

05:48.215 --> 05:51.450
And that's why you're going
to write me a 2,000-word article

05:51.485 --> 05:53.919
on an old-fashioned
American Christmas.

05:53.954 --> 05:56.788
An old-fashioned
American Christmas?

05:56.857 --> 05:58.924
That's both broad and vague.

05:58.992 --> 06:01.326
Think of it as an opportunity
to sit back and reflect

06:01.362 --> 06:03.328
on all the Christmas
traditions

06:03.364 --> 06:04.429
you missed growing up,

06:04.465 --> 06:05.905
and I'm going to need it
on the 23rd.

06:07.301 --> 06:08.934
As an incentive,

06:08.969 --> 06:10.202
and because
I'm also awesome,

06:10.237 --> 06:13.071
I booked you a cabin
in pine grove.

06:13.107 --> 06:14.039
My treat.

06:14.074 --> 06:15.707
This is bribery.

06:15.743 --> 06:16.743
Yes. Yes, it is.

06:25.319 --> 06:27.352
I know that look.
What's up?

06:27.388 --> 06:29.054
I was just thinking

06:29.089 --> 06:30.133
that maybe we could do
something different

06:30.157 --> 06:31.089
this Christmas.

06:31.125 --> 06:32.023
Like, different how?

06:32.059 --> 06:33.125
Like...

06:33.160 --> 06:34.826
Not a hotel for brunch.

06:34.862 --> 06:36.194
Hey, hey, hey.

06:37.965 --> 06:38.997
What's going on?

06:39.066 --> 06:40.632
We had an assignment
in class today.

06:40.701 --> 06:42.200
We could write about anything.

06:42.236 --> 06:43.201
I started thinking
about Christmas.

06:43.237 --> 06:44.603
Oh, yeah?

06:44.671 --> 06:45.637
No, I mean, like...

06:45.672 --> 06:47.739
The ones we used
to have with mom.

06:47.808 --> 06:48.640
We'd go up into
the mountains

06:48.675 --> 06:50.642
and have snow,

06:50.677 --> 06:52.055
and everything smelled
like Christmas trees.

06:52.079 --> 06:53.745
You remember that?

06:53.781 --> 06:54.781
It's fuzzy, but yeah.

06:58.051 --> 07:01.353
"Make cookies.
Build a snowman."

07:03.290 --> 07:05.190
"Gingerbread house."

07:06.927 --> 07:08.160
That was your mom's favorite.

07:11.231 --> 07:12.764
I suppose
you have some place in mind?

07:16.470 --> 07:17.569
[Woman]:
Pine grove?

07:17.638 --> 07:19.115
Apparently,
her best friend from school

07:19.139 --> 07:20.450
has been talking about it
non-stop.

07:20.474 --> 07:21.973
She even made
this "bucket list"

07:22.009 --> 07:23.809
of things to do
to make it the best Christmas,

07:23.844 --> 07:25.004
and most of them
involve snow.

07:26.880 --> 07:31.149
[Mother]:
Oh, Scott, this is so adorable.

07:31.185 --> 07:32.796
I don't think we actually spent
a Christmas

07:32.820 --> 07:34.786
in a cabin in the woods.

07:34.822 --> 07:36.822
Or we just stay here,
you know?

07:36.857 --> 07:38.890
I mean, the important thing
is that we're together.

07:38.926 --> 07:40.403
Yeah, but that's not
what Katy asked for,

07:40.427 --> 07:41.726
and she asks
for so little.

07:43.497 --> 07:44.863
Tell you what.

07:44.898 --> 07:46.142
Why don't I get this
as a Christmas present

07:46.166 --> 07:47.166
for you and Katy?

07:47.201 --> 07:48.166
Mom...

07:48.202 --> 07:49.601
No, I insist.

07:49.636 --> 07:51.970
I'm going to find the most
charming cabin in pine grove

07:52.005 --> 07:52.938
for both of you
to stay in.

07:52.973 --> 07:54.005
What about you?

07:54.074 --> 07:55.351
Well, I've got
Bree tenner's birthday

07:55.375 --> 07:56.375
in a few days,

07:56.410 --> 07:57.676
and I promised I'd attend.

07:57.711 --> 07:59.945
Okay, fine, so you attend,
and then you join us.

08:00.013 --> 08:00.879
I mean, you never go anywhere.

08:00.914 --> 08:02.914
Oh, that is not true.

08:02.983 --> 08:04.616
I went to your aunt
Ruthie's July 4th.

08:04.651 --> 08:06.329
That was three years ago,
and that was in Oakland.

08:06.353 --> 08:07.964
I mean, I basically can see
Oakland from here.

08:07.988 --> 08:09.287
You barely leave
the bay area.

08:09.323 --> 08:11.289
That's because I'm a homebody,
and you know it.

08:11.325 --> 08:12.836
I'm not letting you be alone for
Christmas.

08:12.860 --> 08:15.026
If you don't go,
we don't go.

08:15.062 --> 08:15.894
Scott...

08:15.929 --> 08:16.929
Mom...

08:18.031 --> 08:19.031
Please, Nana?

08:23.003 --> 08:24.247
Now, how am I supposed
to resist that?

08:24.271 --> 08:26.538
You're not.

08:26.573 --> 08:27.573
Oh...

08:28.842 --> 08:30.609
Of course
I'll go.

08:30.677 --> 08:31.677
<i>[Phone ringing]</i>

08:33.981 --> 08:35.179
Hi, dad!

08:35.215 --> 08:36.326
[Dad, on phone]:
<i>Hey there, pumpkin!</i>

08:36.350 --> 08:37.649
How's Hong Kong?

08:37.683 --> 08:39.604
[Dad]: Well, we just got here
a little while ago.

08:40.754 --> 08:42.187
Not too late for you
to join us.

08:42.222 --> 08:44.289
You'll be in meetings
the entire time,

08:44.358 --> 08:46.236
and mom'll be on the phone
dealing with her charities.

08:46.260 --> 08:48.326
<i>Boy, it's as if
you've met us before.</i>

08:48.362 --> 08:49.394
Once or twice.

08:49.463 --> 08:50.595
Mom says hi.

08:50.631 --> 08:52.531
Hi, mom!

08:52.599 --> 08:55.267
No, I'll wait 'til we can take
a real vacation together,

08:55.302 --> 08:56.535
maybe in the spring.

08:56.570 --> 08:58.904
<i>All right, done.
We'll look forward to that.</i>

08:58.939 --> 09:02.240
So, what are you doing
for Christmas, huh?

09:02.309 --> 09:04.876
Are you going to be jetting off
to some far corner of the globe?

09:04.945 --> 09:07.946
Actually, I've rented
a cabin up in pine grove.

09:07.981 --> 09:11.383
Pine grove?

09:11.418 --> 09:12.662
Haven't been there
since you were little.

09:12.686 --> 09:14.419
I've been to pine grove?

09:14.454 --> 09:15.687
<i>You have.</i>

09:15.722 --> 09:17.856
We went there together
for Christmas one year.

09:17.891 --> 09:19.724
You were maybe four or five,
I think?

09:19.793 --> 09:20.926
<i>I don't know.</i>

09:20.961 --> 09:22.338
<i>It was before
I started the company.</i>

09:22.362 --> 09:23.495
I don't remember that.

09:23.530 --> 09:25.630
I do.

09:25.666 --> 09:27.243
Might've been the last
old-fashioned Christmas

09:27.267 --> 09:28.633
we had together.

09:28.702 --> 09:31.403
We had
an old-fashioned Christmas?

09:31.438 --> 09:32.837
We did.

09:32.873 --> 09:33.972
Once upon a time.

09:54.995 --> 09:56.139
It's like I stepped
into another world

09:56.163 --> 09:57.629
made entirely of Christmas.

09:57.698 --> 09:59.931
Did I mention the guy
that I rented the cabin from

09:59.967 --> 10:01.199
also runs the candy store?

10:01.234 --> 10:02.734
Uh, you didn't,

10:02.803 --> 10:04.836
but somehow,
it makes perfect sense.

10:04.871 --> 10:06.349
<i>Maybe it'll be good
for your writing.</i>

10:06.373 --> 10:08.184
Have you figured out your angle
on the article yet?

10:08.208 --> 10:10.809
Uh... nope.

10:10.844 --> 10:12.811
Well, don't over-think it.

10:12.879 --> 10:14.713
<i>Just experience it.
It'll come.</i>

10:14.748 --> 10:16.281
Well, that's just it.

10:16.350 --> 10:19.384
I haven't experienced it...

10:19.419 --> 10:21.987
I mean, not the way
that people think of here.

10:22.022 --> 10:24.089
Italy, Brazil, Tibet?

10:24.124 --> 10:25.090
Sure...

10:25.125 --> 10:26.591
But snowmen and Santa?

10:26.627 --> 10:27.559
I got nothing.

10:27.594 --> 10:28.927
<i>I know,</i>

10:28.962 --> 10:30.239
but at least it sounds
like you're in the right spot

10:30.263 --> 10:31.429
to give it a try,

10:31.498 --> 10:32.430
and who knows?

10:32.499 --> 10:33.798
You may even be inspired

10:33.834 --> 10:36.434
<i>to finish that book idea
we discussed.</i>

10:36.470 --> 10:38.670
Maybe.

10:38.705 --> 10:41.439
That would require me
to stay in one place

10:41.475 --> 10:42.715
for an extended period of time.

10:42.743 --> 10:44.042
It's been known to happen.

10:44.077 --> 10:46.177
To others.

10:46.213 --> 10:47.812
Okay, I've got to go find

10:47.848 --> 10:51.516
this cabin-rental
slash-candy-man.

10:51.551 --> 10:52.817
<i>Ciao!</i>

10:56.390 --> 10:58.757
[♪♪♪]

10:58.792 --> 10:59.891
Excuse me,

10:59.926 --> 11:01.726
do you know where
I can find Hal Hindry?

11:01.762 --> 11:02.861
That would be me.

11:02.896 --> 11:04.396
Oh, great, um...

11:04.464 --> 11:05.541
So I'm Emory Blake,
and I'm...

11:05.565 --> 11:06.731
[Man]:
Hey, Hal?

11:06.767 --> 11:07.777
What do you want me
to do with the posters

11:07.801 --> 11:09.112
for the gingerbread
house contest?

11:09.136 --> 11:10.935
Oh, good!
Hang one in the front window.

11:10.971 --> 11:12.415
Sorry about that.
What was your name again?

11:12.439 --> 11:13.471
Emory...

11:13.540 --> 11:14.773
Excuse me.

11:14.808 --> 11:15.874
Skip!

11:15.909 --> 11:18.043
Can you help Mrs. chase?

11:18.078 --> 11:19.310
It's a crazy time of the year.

11:19.346 --> 11:21.446
I'm just here
to pick up some keys

11:21.481 --> 11:23.615
for a cabin
rented under Emory Blake?

11:23.650 --> 11:24.650
Ah, my other job.

11:24.685 --> 11:25.685
This way.

11:28.455 --> 11:30.188
Ah...

11:30.223 --> 11:32.557
Looks like
you're in cedar bluff.

11:32.592 --> 11:34.225
That's a
wonderful cabin.

11:34.261 --> 11:35.538
Is the other half of your party
with you?

11:35.562 --> 11:37.162
Uh, no.

11:37.197 --> 11:38.763
It's just me.

11:38.799 --> 11:40.131
Is it?

11:40.167 --> 11:41.644
What should I do
with the rest of these?

11:41.668 --> 11:44.035
Hang one in every store window
out by the rec center, then.

11:44.071 --> 11:45.036
- Okay, you got it.
- Sorry.

11:45.072 --> 11:46.705
It's our gingerbread
house contest,

11:46.740 --> 11:49.674
pine grove's version
of the super bowl.

11:51.344 --> 11:53.678
This has everything
you'll need,

11:53.714 --> 11:54.913
and a map to the cabin.

11:54.948 --> 11:57.582
Now, there's
a big snow storm

11:57.617 --> 11:58.950
headed our way soon,

11:58.985 --> 12:01.186
so I hope
you have snow tires.

12:01.221 --> 12:02.854
It's going
to be a doozy.

12:11.264 --> 12:13.465
Right...

12:13.500 --> 12:14.500
There you go.

12:14.534 --> 12:18.536
[♪♪♪]

12:18.572 --> 12:22.140
♪ Gotta try and escape
for Christmas ♪

12:22.175 --> 12:25.577
♪ Lie awake
underneath the moon ♪

12:25.612 --> 12:29.047
♪ Find a place
to leave our troubles ♪

12:29.082 --> 12:32.917
♪ lay under the winter moon ♪

12:32.953 --> 12:34.052
♪ Go easy ♪

12:34.087 --> 12:36.855
♪ And know
I've tried to change ♪

12:36.890 --> 12:39.991
♪ Tried to see it
from the other side ♪

12:40.026 --> 12:42.627
♪ Take it up... ♪

12:42.662 --> 12:44.729
It's snowing!

12:44.765 --> 12:46.197
It is.

12:46.233 --> 12:47.499
All right,
we'd better hurry.

12:47.534 --> 12:49.414
I don't want to be driving
when this gets worse.

12:52.172 --> 12:55.607
♪ ...I won't mind ♪

12:55.642 --> 12:59.144
♪ If you get up
and you walk away ♪

12:59.212 --> 13:03.047
♪ It takes time ♪

13:03.083 --> 13:06.151
♪ To understand me
and love me ♪

13:06.186 --> 13:09.420
♪ I hope you find ♪

13:09.456 --> 13:12.056
♪ That I'm nothing but... ♪

13:12.092 --> 13:14.759
♪ Head over heels
with you ♪♪

13:15.896 --> 13:16.861
[Katy]: Wow!

13:16.897 --> 13:18.263
Neat, huh?

13:18.331 --> 13:19.497
Yeah.

13:22.469 --> 13:23.268
All right.

13:23.303 --> 13:25.670
Huh.

13:25.705 --> 13:27.172
Okay.
There you go.

13:28.441 --> 13:29.641
Thank you.

13:32.279 --> 13:35.180
Wow, this is awesome!
Can I go outside?

13:35.215 --> 13:36.215
Sure.

13:37.484 --> 13:38.883
Just stay close, okay?

13:41.021 --> 13:42.187
I love you,
sweetheart.

13:46.393 --> 13:47.393
All right...

13:48.829 --> 13:51.196
That is not safe.

13:53.366 --> 13:54.699
[Screaming]

13:54.768 --> 13:56.801
My knee!
What the...?

13:56.837 --> 13:58.314
You have ten seconds
to get out of here.

13:58.338 --> 13:59.270
What just happened?

13:59.306 --> 14:00.538
Seriously,

14:00.574 --> 14:02.454
I know krav maga,
and I am not afraid to use it!

14:04.711 --> 14:06.511
There's a sledding hill
out there!

14:06.546 --> 14:07.879
Whoa...

14:07.948 --> 14:10.148
It's okay, honey.
It's... it's okay.

14:10.183 --> 14:11.416
You broke in with a kid?

14:11.451 --> 14:13.218
We didn't break in.
We used a key.

14:13.253 --> 14:14.253
We're renting this place.

14:14.287 --> 14:15.787
This is my place!

14:15.822 --> 14:17.500
I swear, the only thing
I'm reaching for in my coat

14:17.524 --> 14:18.690
is my phone, okay?

14:18.725 --> 14:19.836
I'm going to show you
our booking reservation.

14:19.860 --> 14:20.925
Slowly.

14:20.994 --> 14:22.827
Just a phone.

14:25.599 --> 14:27.932
Booking confirmation.
Hal...

14:27.968 --> 14:29.434
Hindry.

14:29.469 --> 14:31.102
Cabin rentals and candy man.
Yeah.

14:31.137 --> 14:32.470
Pretty sure there's only one.

14:32.539 --> 14:33.739
My confirmation
is right there.

14:33.773 --> 14:34.839
[Scott]:
Great...

14:34.875 --> 14:36.207
So...

14:38.511 --> 14:40.211
So...

14:40.280 --> 14:41.946
So we're all going
to stay here?

14:41.982 --> 14:42.982
No.

14:49.923 --> 14:51.823
Oh, dear.

14:51.858 --> 14:53.791
I am truly, truly sorry.

14:53.827 --> 14:55.260
I don't know how...

14:55.295 --> 14:56.906
Skip, put the licorice
on the top shelf...

14:56.930 --> 14:58.796
This happened.

14:58.832 --> 14:59.832
It's a mystery.

14:59.900 --> 15:01.266
The important thing here

15:01.301 --> 15:03.101
is that we have
a place for Ms. Blake to stay.

15:03.737 --> 15:05.081
Oh, um, you're just
going to assume

15:05.105 --> 15:06.170
that I'm the one

15:06.206 --> 15:07.526
that's going to
give up the cabin?

15:08.074 --> 15:09.074
I have a kid.

15:11.177 --> 15:13.444
Seriously?

15:13.480 --> 15:15.124
You don't even hesitate
to play the kid card?

15:15.148 --> 15:16.281
My mom comes in tomorrow.

15:16.316 --> 15:19.017
Yeah, well...

15:19.052 --> 15:20.184
Your confirmation says

15:20.220 --> 15:21.719
that you booked
just two days ago,

15:21.755 --> 15:23.154
which means I booked first.

15:23.189 --> 15:24.600
There are three
bedrooms in this house,

15:24.624 --> 15:26.491
which is too big
for one person.

15:26.526 --> 15:27.492
I rest my case.

15:27.527 --> 15:28.593
Are you an attorney?

15:28.628 --> 15:30.061
I am.

15:30.096 --> 15:32.297
That makes me want
to stay put even more.

15:32.365 --> 15:33.564
[Scott]:
What do you do?

15:33.600 --> 15:34.532
Travel writer.

15:34.567 --> 15:36.034
Perfect.

15:36.069 --> 15:37.647
I'm sure you're accustomed
to accommodation inconveniences.

15:37.671 --> 15:39.337
Yep, so I can tell you
from experience,

15:39.372 --> 15:40.416
that you're going
to have no trouble

15:40.440 --> 15:42.440
finding someplace else.

15:42.475 --> 15:45.143
I'm terribly sorry,
but there are no other cabins.

15:45.211 --> 15:47.045
[Together]: None?

15:47.080 --> 15:48.591
Pine grove is booked solid
at Christmas

15:48.615 --> 15:49.781
months in advance.

15:49.849 --> 15:52.884
The only reason cedar bluff
was available

15:52.919 --> 15:54.163
was because
of a last-minute cancellation.

15:54.187 --> 15:55.187
Okay.

15:55.221 --> 15:56.621
What about
someplace else?

15:56.656 --> 15:59.157
I called around as soon
as you told me what happened.

15:59.225 --> 16:00.325
There's nothing.

16:00.393 --> 16:03.261
I'm so terribly sorry.

16:03.296 --> 16:04.228
Where do I put
the white chocolate pretzels?

16:04.264 --> 16:05.229
Up front.

16:05.265 --> 16:06.731
Right over here, skip.

16:12.205 --> 16:13.404
Oh...

16:15.141 --> 16:17.542
So there are no rooms
at any inn.

16:17.577 --> 16:18.910
Strangely appropriate.

16:18.945 --> 16:20.678
Mm.

16:20.714 --> 16:22.074
This would be perfect
for sledding.

16:24.184 --> 16:25.184
C'mon...

16:26.653 --> 16:29.020
Ugh, fine.
Kid card wins.

16:29.089 --> 16:31.489
I'll head back
to San Francisco

16:31.558 --> 16:33.758
with my Christmas cabin
experiment

16:33.793 --> 16:35.326
officially over.

16:35.362 --> 16:36.894
But it's snowing
really hard.

16:36.930 --> 16:37.695
You didn't want to drive when
it was snowing bad, remember?

16:37.731 --> 16:38.896
[Emory]:
Katy, don't worry.

16:38.965 --> 16:40.276
I've motorcycled
through the Andes.

16:40.300 --> 16:41.300
I can handle this.

16:41.334 --> 16:43.468
Yeah, see?

16:43.503 --> 16:45.303
She'll be fine.

16:45.338 --> 16:47.638
Thanks for this.

16:49.109 --> 16:51.109
All right, hays family,

16:51.177 --> 16:52.177
merry Christmas,

16:52.212 --> 16:53.878
and, uh...

16:53.913 --> 16:55.113
Enjoy my cabin.

16:55.148 --> 16:56.447
Our cabin.

16:56.483 --> 16:58.116
Ha...

16:58.151 --> 17:00.218
Hey, thanks again.
We appreciate it.

17:04.624 --> 17:05.624
Whew!

17:07.426 --> 17:09.359
[Engine sputtering]

17:10.730 --> 17:12.829
Oh, no...

17:12.866 --> 17:15.500
Please don't be like this.

17:15.568 --> 17:17.969
[Engine sputtering]

17:18.038 --> 17:19.936
Dad?

17:20.006 --> 17:22.406
Start, start, start...

17:22.442 --> 17:23.508
Ugh...

17:23.542 --> 17:25.276
[Engine starting and humming]

17:25.310 --> 17:26.344
[Exhaling]

17:26.378 --> 17:27.645
[Engine sputtering
and dying]

17:27.680 --> 17:28.680
Oh...

17:30.350 --> 17:31.350
[Horn honking]

17:36.423 --> 17:38.222
[Knocking]

17:41.928 --> 17:43.027
How's it going?

17:43.096 --> 17:45.596
Oh, she just gets
a little, uh, sensitive

17:45.632 --> 17:46.632
when it's cold.

17:47.734 --> 17:49.134
Well, it's only going
to get colder.

17:50.136 --> 17:52.036
Fair point.

17:52.072 --> 17:54.739
Why don't you come back
and stay at the cabin

17:54.808 --> 17:56.874
until the storm passes?

17:56.943 --> 17:57.943
Just for tonight.

17:58.978 --> 18:01.245
Just for tonight.

18:08.855 --> 18:11.556
[Wind blowing]

18:11.591 --> 18:12.924
I will be out of here

18:12.959 --> 18:15.093
just as soon as
the shop gives me the okay.

18:15.161 --> 18:16.727
It's the alternator.

18:17.730 --> 18:18.730
How can you tell?

18:18.798 --> 18:20.064
You can hear it.

18:20.133 --> 18:22.166
You're both a lawyer
and a mechanic?

18:22.202 --> 18:23.879
No, my dad and I used
to tinker around with cars

18:23.903 --> 18:24.903
when I was younger.

18:25.805 --> 18:27.738
Huh.

18:27.774 --> 18:29.407
Expand on the "huh."

18:29.442 --> 18:31.609
You don't seem like a car guy.

18:31.644 --> 18:32.743
How can you tell?

18:32.812 --> 18:34.078
We just met.

18:34.147 --> 18:36.114
What, you don't get
first impressions of people?

18:36.149 --> 18:37.348
No, not that specific.

18:37.417 --> 18:38.850
Hey, are you sure

18:38.918 --> 18:39.784
you don't want
to sleep upstairs

18:39.819 --> 18:40.618
in the extra bedroom?

18:40.653 --> 18:42.386
Oh, no.

18:42.422 --> 18:43.754
Your mom's coming tomorrow.

18:43.790 --> 18:45.690
This way, the room'll be
nice and fresh for her.

18:45.725 --> 18:47.258
Okay.

18:47.327 --> 18:49.627
Besides, I like
sleeping next to a fire.

18:49.662 --> 18:52.697
Next to the net of a catamaran
in the Caribbean,

18:52.765 --> 18:54.143
I'd say it's my favorite place
to sleep.

18:54.167 --> 18:55.633
The net of a catamaran?

18:55.668 --> 18:57.135
[Laughing]

18:57.203 --> 18:58.136
Don't knock it.

18:58.204 --> 18:59.871
Once you fall asleep

18:59.906 --> 19:02.673
with Orion
coming over the ocean horizon,

19:02.709 --> 19:04.542
you realize
you just fulfilled a dream

19:04.577 --> 19:05.843
you never knew you had.

19:05.879 --> 19:07.111
All right,
I'm starting

19:07.147 --> 19:09.347
to get a small sense
of who you are.

19:09.415 --> 19:10.148
You're adventurous.

19:10.183 --> 19:11.916
I am.

19:11.951 --> 19:14.118
Rarely in one place
for too long.

19:14.187 --> 19:15.353
All my life.

19:15.388 --> 19:16.354
Army brat?

19:16.389 --> 19:18.055
Sort of...

19:18.091 --> 19:19.724
Minus the army.

19:21.394 --> 19:23.794
My parents worked
in international finance.

19:23.830 --> 19:25.141
I grew up traveling
my whole life.

19:25.165 --> 19:26.165
Mm.

19:28.434 --> 19:30.368
And tomorrow,
I'm hitting the road again.

19:31.571 --> 19:32.815
Thanks again
for letting us stay.

19:32.839 --> 19:34.405
No, thank you.

19:36.509 --> 19:37.475
Sleep well.

19:37.510 --> 19:39.010
Good night.

19:41.014 --> 19:43.881
[♪♪♪]

19:53.660 --> 19:54.660
[Floorboard squeaking]

19:59.632 --> 20:01.065
Sorry.

20:01.100 --> 20:03.000
Don't be.

20:03.036 --> 20:04.969
I was just about awake anyway.

20:05.004 --> 20:07.471
Are those from all
the places you've been?

20:07.507 --> 20:08.873
Uh...

20:08.942 --> 20:11.742
Some of the places
I've been, yeah.

20:11.778 --> 20:14.078
I want to travel one day,

20:14.113 --> 20:15.012
see everything.

20:15.048 --> 20:15.913
Oh, yeah?

20:15.949 --> 20:17.648
There's a lot to see.

20:20.053 --> 20:22.887
Would you want to look through
some of my travel photos

20:22.956 --> 20:24.155
while I go get cleaned up?

20:24.190 --> 20:25.756
Really?

20:25.792 --> 20:27.091
Yeah, sure.

20:27.126 --> 20:28.126
Here.

20:29.762 --> 20:31.562
There you go.

20:31.598 --> 20:33.097
Have at it.

20:48.014 --> 20:49.792
[Scott's mother]:
I think you made the right call.

20:49.816 --> 20:51.260
I'm monitoring
the weather conditions,

20:51.284 --> 20:53.584
and it looks like all the roads
going into the mountains

20:53.620 --> 20:54.652
are closed right now.

20:54.687 --> 20:56.254
Well, how long
is that going to last?

20:56.289 --> 20:57.822
Mm, at least a day
to clear them?

20:57.890 --> 20:59.290
That's what I read.

20:59.359 --> 21:01.036
So your guest is stuck,
even if her car is ready today.

21:01.060 --> 21:03.494
[Sighing]

21:03.529 --> 21:05.129
What's with that expression?

21:05.164 --> 21:06.164
Nothing.

21:06.199 --> 21:07.164
<i>Don't "nothing" me.</i>

21:07.200 --> 21:08.299
I raised you.

21:08.334 --> 21:10.034
Is there something wrong
with this woman?

21:10.103 --> 21:11.103
No.
She's, uh...

21:12.305 --> 21:13.237
Pleasant.

21:13.273 --> 21:14.805
Pleasant?

21:14.874 --> 21:15.874
Hmm.

21:15.908 --> 21:17.275
What's her name again?

21:17.343 --> 21:18.409
<i>Emory Blake.</i>

21:18.444 --> 21:19.377
<i>She's a travel writer...</i>

21:19.412 --> 21:20.344
And no, it's fine.

21:20.380 --> 21:21.812
It's just unexpected.

21:23.349 --> 21:24.649
[Phone chiming]

21:24.684 --> 21:26.117
[Chuckling]

21:26.152 --> 21:27.885
Your granddaughter
just texted me,

21:27.920 --> 21:29.854
demanding breakfast in bed.

21:29.889 --> 21:31.756
Oh.
Well then, you'd better go.

21:31.791 --> 21:32.857
I'll let you know

21:32.892 --> 21:34.558
as soon as
I'm on the way to you, okay?

21:34.594 --> 21:35.626
Love you.

21:35.662 --> 21:36.662
[Chiming]

21:38.164 --> 21:40.364
Emory... Blake...

21:44.804 --> 21:47.238
Pleasant.

21:47.273 --> 21:48.539
Hmm.

21:59.886 --> 22:01.385
- Oh!
- Whoo!

22:01.421 --> 22:03.087
I'm sorry.

22:03.122 --> 22:04.422
It's okay.

22:04.490 --> 22:06.001
At least you didn't hit me
with krav maga this time.

22:06.025 --> 22:07.525
The day is young.

22:07.560 --> 22:08.726
Well, good.

22:08.761 --> 22:09.938
Then I have something
to look forward to.

22:09.962 --> 22:11.996
Well, I plan on spending
the day writing.

22:12.065 --> 22:13.264
I've got my eye

22:13.299 --> 22:14.510
on this little office
attic space up there,

22:14.534 --> 22:16.567
and I claim dibs,

22:16.602 --> 22:17.935
so please don't get any ideas.

22:18.004 --> 22:19.236
It is all yours.

22:19.272 --> 22:20.649
Katy and I will be working
on her bucket list.

22:20.673 --> 22:21.673
Her what?

22:21.708 --> 22:23.107
It's her list

22:23.142 --> 22:25.187
of all the awesome things
she wants to do for Christmas.

22:25.211 --> 22:26.477
Oh, well...

22:26.512 --> 22:27.912
You'd better get cracking.

22:27.947 --> 22:29.613
All right.
We'll stay out of your way.

22:29.649 --> 22:30.781
Yeah, good luck.

22:35.421 --> 22:39.423
♪ I don't want
much for Christmas ♪

22:39.459 --> 22:43.494
♪ I love Louis
and I love Dior ♪

22:43.563 --> 22:47.598
♪ But I've got my heart
set on something different ♪

22:47.633 --> 22:51.836
♪ One special thing
I've been wishing for ♪

22:51.871 --> 22:55.606
♪ I've been waiting
all year long ♪

22:55.641 --> 22:58.476
♪ Underneath the mistletoe
the time has come ♪

22:58.511 --> 23:00.211
[Door slamming]

23:00.246 --> 23:03.381
♪ Santa gave me
just one wish ♪

23:03.416 --> 23:04.715
[Katy and Scott talking]

23:04.751 --> 23:07.618
♪ Baby, I want
your Christmas kiss ♪

23:07.653 --> 23:09.487
[Katy and Scott talking]

23:16.929 --> 23:20.831
♪ I think I found
my perfect present ♪

23:20.867 --> 23:25.002
♪ Wrap you up
and put you under my tree... ♪

23:26.773 --> 23:27.738
Whatcha looking at, buddy?

23:27.774 --> 23:29.073
Emory let me look at it.

23:29.108 --> 23:30.908
It's all her travel photos.

23:30.943 --> 23:33.043
Oh.

23:33.079 --> 23:35.546
These are from Christmas
all around the world.

23:35.581 --> 23:36.747
Quite a few photos here.

23:38.618 --> 23:40.985
Yeah, I want to travel a lot.

23:41.020 --> 23:42.286
Really?

23:42.321 --> 23:44.655
But then I would spend
all of my time going,

23:44.724 --> 23:46.123
"where's Katy?

23:46.159 --> 23:47.691
What is she doing?

23:47.727 --> 23:48.937
Is she having fun?
Is she safe?"

23:48.961 --> 23:49.894
[Mock-sobbing]

23:49.929 --> 23:51.695
It's okay.

23:51.731 --> 23:54.231
I'll come back
every Christmas.

23:54.300 --> 23:56.133
I'm holding you to that.

23:56.169 --> 23:57.601
- Okay.
- Okay.

23:57.637 --> 23:58.637
Okay!

24:14.787 --> 24:18.622
[Katy]: I'm so excited.
We're finally doing this.

24:18.691 --> 24:20.569
[Scott]: All right,
so you're going to be doing it.

24:20.593 --> 24:21.904
I'm going to let you
cut down this tree

24:21.928 --> 24:22.993
with your big old muscles.

24:23.029 --> 24:23.994
[Katy]: Yeah!

24:24.030 --> 24:25.596
[Scott laughs]

24:34.740 --> 24:36.674
Why do you have a saw?

24:36.709 --> 24:37.575
Well, cutting down a tree
with my bare hands

24:37.643 --> 24:38.676
is ineffective.

24:38.711 --> 24:39.810
Ha ha...

24:39.846 --> 24:41.378
Don't quit your day job,
counselor.

24:41.447 --> 24:42.658
We're getting
our Christmas tree.

24:42.682 --> 24:43.926
[Scott]:
There's a tree farm near town

24:43.950 --> 24:45.761
where you can cut down
your own Christmas tree.

24:45.785 --> 24:48.085
And I've wanted to do this
my whole life.

24:48.120 --> 24:49.520
Ha, that long, huh?

24:49.555 --> 24:50.866
Have you ever cut down
a Christmas tree?

24:50.890 --> 24:51.922
I have to say,

24:51.991 --> 24:53.991
in my whole life,
I have not.

24:54.026 --> 24:55.125
Is it fun?

24:55.161 --> 24:56.427
Well, we're about to find out.

24:56.462 --> 24:57.695
It's our new tradition.

24:57.763 --> 24:59.430
Isn't that an oxymoron?

24:59.465 --> 25:00.631
So we've never
done it before,

25:00.666 --> 25:01.932
but the tradition is old.

25:01.968 --> 25:03.234
[Emory]: right.

25:03.269 --> 25:06.036
Old-fashioned...

25:06.072 --> 25:07.538
Which I saw
on your list in there.

25:07.573 --> 25:09.173
I took a little peek.

25:09.208 --> 25:10.374
It's very thorough.

25:10.443 --> 25:11.775
Very long as well,

25:11.811 --> 25:13.978
so...
We're going to get going.

25:14.013 --> 25:15.479
Right, um,
so, ha...

25:15.548 --> 25:17.314
Here's the deal.

25:17.383 --> 25:18.516
I have to write an article

25:18.551 --> 25:20.162
about an old-fashioned
American Christmas,

25:20.186 --> 25:21.552
and, uh...

25:21.587 --> 25:22.865
I haven't been in the states
for Christmas

25:22.889 --> 25:25.489
in, well, forever.

25:26.526 --> 25:28.592
So...

25:30.096 --> 25:31.139
What are you trying to say?

25:31.163 --> 25:34.231
Could I... tag along?

25:34.267 --> 25:36.166
Just to observe.

25:36.202 --> 25:37.312
You want to observe
our Christmas?

25:37.336 --> 25:38.802
Just to get
some inspiration?

25:38.838 --> 25:41.205
I think your list is exactly
what I need.

25:41.274 --> 25:42.940
Christmas
is for sharing.

25:42.975 --> 25:44.308
See?

25:44.343 --> 25:45.676
Right there.

25:45.745 --> 25:47.044
That is what
I am talking about.

25:48.381 --> 25:49.246
Yeah, fine.

25:49.282 --> 25:50.915
Observe.

25:50.950 --> 25:52.850
Great!
Thank you.

25:52.885 --> 25:54.196
I'm just going to grab
some gloves and a hat,

25:54.220 --> 25:56.140
and... one second.
Please don't leave without me!

26:13.105 --> 26:14.338
These are nice.

26:14.373 --> 26:16.373
You guys like
any of these?

26:16.409 --> 26:17.341
[Together]: That one.

26:17.376 --> 26:19.476
[Laughing]

26:19.512 --> 26:20.678
That one it is.

26:20.713 --> 26:22.146
Okay...

26:22.181 --> 26:23.981
Can Emory cut it down?

26:24.016 --> 26:25.649
I thought this was something

26:25.718 --> 26:27.084
you wanted
to do your whole life.

26:27.119 --> 26:28.619
Well, yeah, but...

26:28.688 --> 26:29.920
You need help
with your story,

26:29.956 --> 26:31.488
and besides, I have more time.

26:31.524 --> 26:32.823
[Snickering]

26:32.858 --> 26:33.958
Hey, you
watch it, pal.

26:33.993 --> 26:35.492
We're about the same age.

26:35.528 --> 26:37.428
Are you sure?

26:37.463 --> 26:38.562
What?
You think I can't?

26:38.598 --> 26:40.331
[Scott]: No, you seem
like you could do

26:40.399 --> 26:41.443
anything
you put your mind to.

26:41.467 --> 26:43.567
Mm, how would you know?
We just met.

26:43.603 --> 26:45.180
Been around you long enough
to form an opinion

26:45.204 --> 26:46.882
based on observation
and empirical evidence.

26:46.906 --> 26:48.072
Oof, there's the attorney.

26:50.009 --> 26:51.153
By the way, the garage called
when you were in the shower.

26:51.177 --> 26:52.209
It's the alternator.

26:52.278 --> 26:53.944
Hmm.

26:53.980 --> 26:55.357
Bet you're proud of yourself,
aren't you?

26:55.381 --> 26:56.614
It feels pretty good.

26:56.649 --> 26:58.949
It'll be fixed by tomorrow,
but until then...

27:00.186 --> 27:01.719
Thank you.
Oh!

27:01.754 --> 27:02.686
Would you take my picture?

27:02.722 --> 27:03.722
Yeah.

27:08.861 --> 27:10.394
Oh, right, um...

27:10.429 --> 27:12.196
It's an actual camera.

27:12.231 --> 27:13.564
You just point
and shoot.

27:15.067 --> 27:16.867
[Katy]: You just press
the button?

27:16.902 --> 27:18.135
Okay.

27:18.170 --> 27:18.902
[Scott]: Little different
than your phone, huh?

27:18.971 --> 27:19.870
[Katy]: Yeah.

27:19.905 --> 27:20.938
[Sawing]

27:20.973 --> 27:22.006
[Emory]:
All right, guys.

27:22.041 --> 27:23.041
[Camera clicking]

27:23.075 --> 27:24.341
Here goes nothing.

27:24.410 --> 27:25.643
[Creaking]

27:26.879 --> 27:27.811
[Camera clicking]

27:27.880 --> 27:28.880
Ha ha...
Oh!

27:30.449 --> 27:31.582
There we have it!

27:31.651 --> 27:32.549
Nice work.

27:32.585 --> 27:33.884
Thank you.

27:33.919 --> 27:35.119
[Scott]: You did it.
All right.

27:36.789 --> 27:38.689
[Emory]:
That is a beautiful tree.

27:38.758 --> 27:40.057
All right,
one more picture?

27:40.092 --> 27:42.526
[Katy]:
Stand next to the tree.

27:42.561 --> 27:43.927
Right.

27:46.332 --> 27:47.865
You too, dad.

27:52.371 --> 27:53.470
[Laughing] Okay.

27:53.506 --> 27:54.672
Say cheese!

27:54.740 --> 27:55.806
Cheese...

27:55.841 --> 27:56.841
Or Christmas tree!

27:56.876 --> 27:58.575
[Camera clicking]

27:58.611 --> 28:00.355
It's fun having a real one
to play around with.

28:00.379 --> 28:01.879
Oh, yeah?

28:01.914 --> 28:02.980
You can keep it.

28:03.015 --> 28:03.881
[Scott]:
Oh, no, hey, that's...

28:03.916 --> 28:05.282
No, come on.

28:05.317 --> 28:06.684
'Tis the season,
and all that.

28:06.719 --> 28:07.959
I took
a lot of my travel photos

28:07.987 --> 28:09.186
with that camera.

28:09.255 --> 28:10.255
It's good luck.

28:11.791 --> 28:12.956
Thank you so much!

28:12.992 --> 28:13.757
All right, I think I'm
going to need some help

28:13.793 --> 28:15.125
carrying this tree.

28:15.194 --> 28:16.060
I got this.
I got it.

28:16.095 --> 28:17.494
Thank you!

28:17.530 --> 28:18.729
Follow me.

28:18.798 --> 28:19.830
You excited?

28:19.865 --> 28:21.365
Yeah.

28:21.400 --> 28:22.633
Let's take this home.

28:25.971 --> 28:27.271
Katy!

28:27.306 --> 28:29.139
Johnny!

28:29.208 --> 28:31.675
Well, well,
look who we have here.

28:32.812 --> 28:33.911
Why didn't
you tell me

28:33.979 --> 28:34.745
you were coming to
my neck of the woods?

28:34.814 --> 28:36.046
I'm sorry.

28:36.115 --> 28:37.315
I just got
a little distracted.

28:38.050 --> 28:40.150
I see.

28:40.186 --> 28:41.752
Hi. I'm Alice.
Alice Bennett.

28:41.787 --> 28:42.920
My son, Johnny,

28:42.955 --> 28:44.366
goes to school with
Scott's daughter.

28:44.390 --> 28:45.723
Oh, great!

28:45.758 --> 28:47.224
Hi. I'm Emory Blake.

28:48.427 --> 28:50.027
So, are you guys here together?

28:50.062 --> 28:51.328
[Together]: No.

28:51.363 --> 28:52.841
No, we had a mix-up
with our cabin rental.

28:52.865 --> 28:54.198
[Emory]:
Double-booked,

28:54.266 --> 28:55.410
and then my car had troubles,

28:55.434 --> 28:56.578
and I got stuck
by the snowstorm.

28:56.602 --> 28:58.268
Oh...

28:58.304 --> 28:59.536
That's unfortunate.

28:59.572 --> 29:01.872
But I'm heading back
to San Francisco

29:01.907 --> 29:03.107
as soon as possible.

29:03.175 --> 29:05.342
Oh, what a shame
you won't be here for Christmas.

29:05.377 --> 29:07.811
Pine grove is just
magical this time of year.

29:07.847 --> 29:09.313
I'm so glad
that you and Katy

29:09.348 --> 29:10.992
- are finally getting to see it.
- It was about time.

29:11.016 --> 29:12.461
I've been hearing you talk
about it long enough.

29:12.485 --> 29:14.085
Yeah, I practically deserve
a commission.

29:14.120 --> 29:15.753
I don't think
Hal would like that.

29:15.788 --> 29:17.388
Oh, so you met Hal!
Isn't his shop great?

29:17.423 --> 29:18.555
Johnny makes sure

29:18.591 --> 29:19.935
it's our first stop
every time we come.

29:19.959 --> 29:21.725
I'm sure
it'll be Katy's, too.

29:21.794 --> 29:24.094
Although his record-keeping
could use a little work.

29:27.333 --> 29:29.032
All right, well...

29:29.068 --> 29:30.268
We should get this thing home.

29:30.302 --> 29:32.069
Okay, well,
now that we know you're here,

29:32.104 --> 29:33.403
I'll be in touch.

29:33.439 --> 29:35.506
There are so many fun events
you shouldn't miss.

29:35.541 --> 29:36.373
It was really nice to meet you,
Emory.

29:36.408 --> 29:38.041
You, too.

29:38.110 --> 29:39.110
[Scott]:
Great.

29:40.579 --> 29:41.579
Hey, my man.

29:43.048 --> 29:44.088
All right,
let's go, kiddo.

29:51.657 --> 29:53.034
[Katy]: I'll go get
more Christmas lights.

29:53.058 --> 29:54.858
Perfect.

29:54.927 --> 29:56.126
That is a
good-looking tree,

29:56.162 --> 29:56.994
if I do say so myself.

29:57.062 --> 29:57.995
And you did.

29:58.063 --> 30:00.197
And I did.

30:00.232 --> 30:02.410
You know, I think Alice thought
it was good-looking, too...

30:02.434 --> 30:05.068
Amongst
other things.

30:05.137 --> 30:07.271
I'm just saying,
she's very pretty,

30:07.306 --> 30:09.706
and... very interested in you.

30:09.775 --> 30:11.809
She is a parent
at Katy's school.

30:11.844 --> 30:13.255
See how much you guys
have in common?

30:13.279 --> 30:14.411
It's not like that.

30:14.446 --> 30:15.946
Okay.

30:19.919 --> 30:21.018
The thing is,

30:21.053 --> 30:22.686
I haven't really dated
in a long time.

30:26.425 --> 30:28.258
My wife passed away
when Katy was six.

30:28.294 --> 30:29.593
Oh.

30:31.197 --> 30:32.496
I'm so sorry.
I just assumed...

30:32.531 --> 30:35.032
But Katy told me
that Christmas in the mountains

30:35.067 --> 30:37.167
was the one thing
that she could remember

30:37.203 --> 30:38.203
about her mom.

30:40.606 --> 30:41.738
Now I see.

30:41.774 --> 30:43.540
And so she came up
with this list...

30:45.878 --> 30:47.678
And that's why you're here.

30:47.713 --> 30:49.246
That's why we're here.

30:51.951 --> 30:54.051
Nana's going
to love this tree.

30:55.788 --> 30:58.088
All right, what do we
have on that list?

30:58.123 --> 30:59.523
Building a gingerbread house.

30:59.592 --> 31:01.124
Oh!

31:01.160 --> 31:01.925
I saw that there's
a gingerbread house contest

31:01.961 --> 31:02.961
in town.

31:03.963 --> 31:05.762
Dad, we have to do it.

31:05.798 --> 31:07.564
Oh, we have to?
It's a requirement?

31:07.600 --> 31:09.700
Yes.
It's number four.

31:11.437 --> 31:12.437
It's number four.

31:12.471 --> 31:13.370
Well, then you've got to.

31:13.439 --> 31:14.771
All right,

31:14.807 --> 31:15.817
what else do we have
to look forward to?

31:15.841 --> 31:16.841
Baking cookies...

31:16.876 --> 31:17.975
Naturally.

31:18.043 --> 31:19.309
Hanging lights
around the cabin.

31:19.378 --> 31:20.344
Happening.

31:20.379 --> 31:21.945
Also...
Ice skating.

31:22.014 --> 31:23.580
Oh, good.
I saw a rink on the way in.

31:23.649 --> 31:24.715
Do you ice skate?

31:25.985 --> 31:26.985
Um...

31:29.455 --> 31:31.121
I've watched
a lot of ice skating

31:31.156 --> 31:32.589
when I lived in Finland.

31:32.625 --> 31:34.524
It's not really
the same thing.

31:34.560 --> 31:36.193
You think?

31:46.639 --> 31:47.871
Katy!

31:50.709 --> 31:51.842
Okay...

31:51.877 --> 31:52.997
All right, have fun.
Be safe.

31:55.247 --> 31:56.380
You too.

31:57.549 --> 31:59.149
Okay. Here
goes nothing.

32:10.396 --> 32:11.461
You okay?

32:11.497 --> 32:13.664
Uh... just a bruised ego.

32:13.699 --> 32:15.299
[Laughing]

32:15.334 --> 32:16.934
You're not supposed
to laugh.

32:16.969 --> 32:18.936
You get points
for determination.

32:18.971 --> 32:20.348
Yes, well, that is
one of my skills...

32:20.372 --> 32:21.438
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

32:21.507 --> 32:23.206
Unlike ice skating.

32:23.242 --> 32:25.742
I will be doing
a triple Axel in no time.

32:25.811 --> 32:27.477
Yes, because you have
an amazing coach.

32:27.513 --> 32:29.513
Because I am
a warrior

32:29.581 --> 32:32.049
when it comes
to a challenge.

32:34.286 --> 32:35.385
[Alice]: Scott!

32:35.421 --> 32:36.453
Hey, Alice.

32:36.522 --> 32:37.721
Hey!

32:37.756 --> 32:39.222
Hi!

32:39.258 --> 32:41.792
We are seeing you
everywhere.

32:41.827 --> 32:43.193
Hi, Emily!

32:43.262 --> 32:44.628
Uh, Emory.

32:44.663 --> 32:46.296
Oh! Sorry.

32:46.332 --> 32:47.831
Good news!

32:47.900 --> 32:49.533
One of the roads
has opened up,

32:49.568 --> 32:50.467
so you should be able
to head home

32:50.536 --> 32:51.401
as soon as your car's fixed.

32:51.437 --> 32:52.736
Oh, fantastic.

32:52.771 --> 32:53.937
Also fantastic...

32:54.006 --> 32:55.539
I scored
two extra tickets

32:55.574 --> 32:56.952
to the local production
of "the nutcracker."

32:56.976 --> 32:59.343
I would've gotten a fifth,

32:59.378 --> 33:01.323
but I assumed that you would be
going home by then.

33:01.347 --> 33:03.213
Oh, of course.

33:03.248 --> 33:05.882
So it's, um, tomorrow night.

33:05.918 --> 33:06.950
What do you say?

33:07.019 --> 33:08.518
You and me,
Katy and Johnny?

33:12.057 --> 33:13.223
Sounds amazing.

33:13.292 --> 33:14.791
Great, then it's a date!

33:16.095 --> 33:17.427
See you then!

33:21.567 --> 33:23.700
"Date" is just
a figure of speech.

33:23.736 --> 33:26.803
One often associated
with going on a date.

33:26.839 --> 33:28.605
Yeah, but it's...
I mean, it's not a date.

33:28.640 --> 33:31.141
Right.

33:31.176 --> 33:33.877
Little pro tip
from a woman's P.O.V.?

33:33.912 --> 33:36.947
She thinks it's a date.

33:40.552 --> 33:43.020
All right,
triple Axel time.

33:43.055 --> 33:44.287
Whoa...

33:44.323 --> 33:45.589
Whoa!

33:51.397 --> 33:52.996
[Editor]:
<i>So, what are you doing now?</i>

33:53.032 --> 33:54.476
<i>Following them around
and taking notes?</i>

33:54.500 --> 33:58.035
No, I'm participating in parts
of Katy's Christmas list.

33:58.070 --> 33:59.302
Oh, good.

33:59.338 --> 34:00.338
<i>I told you,</i>

34:00.372 --> 34:02.439
I cut down the tree.

34:02.474 --> 34:04.141
And I'm very proud.

34:04.209 --> 34:05.809
Is it helping?
With the article?

34:05.878 --> 34:07.344
You know, it is, actually.

34:07.379 --> 34:08.879
I had
a mostly productive morning.

34:08.914 --> 34:10.246
That's encouraging.

34:10.315 --> 34:12.849
You know...
And it's been fun.

34:12.885 --> 34:14.650
Really?

34:14.686 --> 34:16.119
<i>Yeah, I mean...</i>

34:16.155 --> 34:17.821
Bruises
from the ice skating aside.

34:17.889 --> 34:18.755
Naturally.

34:18.791 --> 34:20.157
<i>Plus,</i>

34:20.225 --> 34:22.391
it was very entertaining
watching Scott try to pretend

34:22.428 --> 34:24.226
this whole
Alice-nutcracker thing

34:24.263 --> 34:25.362
isn't a date

34:25.397 --> 34:27.164
when it so obviously is.

34:27.199 --> 34:29.299
That doesn't bother you,
does it?

34:29.333 --> 34:30.333
What?

34:30.369 --> 34:31.568
No.

34:31.603 --> 34:32.636
I mean...

34:32.670 --> 34:34.438
Sure, he's a nice guy,

34:34.473 --> 34:37.107
albeit pretty goofy at times,

34:37.141 --> 34:38.485
but, you know, he should date
whoever he wants.

34:38.510 --> 34:39.876
And you're sure that's not you?

34:41.246 --> 34:43.179
I'm sure.

34:43.215 --> 34:45.482
Anyway, I'm leaving just as soon
as his mother gets here.

34:45.516 --> 34:47.350
What's keeping you there now?

34:47.418 --> 34:48.552
Oh, well, I promised Katy

34:48.587 --> 34:49.864
that I'd help her
decorate the tree

34:49.888 --> 34:51.554
once her grandma gets here...

34:51.590 --> 34:54.324
Which is the quintessential
Christmas experience, right?

34:54.359 --> 34:57.060
Especially with a cute kid
and her handsome single father.

34:57.129 --> 34:58.695
I never said he was handsome.

34:58.730 --> 35:00.030
Is he?

35:01.700 --> 35:04.401
Only in the most conventional
sense of the word.

35:04.436 --> 35:07.070
Meaning obvious
to those who have eyes.

35:07.106 --> 35:08.071
Correct.

35:08.107 --> 35:09.172
So, he's handsome.

35:10.242 --> 35:11.208
Correct.

35:11.243 --> 35:12.642
And you like him.

35:15.013 --> 35:16.024
<i>I believe the word
you're searching for</i>

35:16.048 --> 35:18.014
is "correct".

35:18.083 --> 35:19.983
Veronica,
if you could see this woman

35:20.052 --> 35:21.918
he doesn't realize
he's going on a date with...

35:21.954 --> 35:23.553
I mean, she's perfection.

35:23.589 --> 35:25.589
Nice dodge,
and no one's perfect.

35:25.657 --> 35:27.290
<i>Alice is close.</i>

35:27.326 --> 35:29.392
She's pretty and nice

35:29.461 --> 35:31.128
and has her own cute kid...

35:31.163 --> 35:34.464
I mean, she's exactly what
a guy like Scott would want.

35:34.500 --> 35:36.099
But do they have chemistry?

35:36.135 --> 35:37.200
Because, like I said,

35:37.236 --> 35:39.402
you can't fake chemistry.

35:40.672 --> 35:42.139
[Vehicle driving up]

35:49.448 --> 35:50.547
We made it...

35:50.582 --> 35:51.748
We made it.

35:51.783 --> 35:52.883
And it was worth it.

35:52.918 --> 35:53.884
- This place is beautiful.
- Isn't it lovely?

35:53.919 --> 35:56.353
Oh, my goodness.

35:56.388 --> 35:57.854
I've got to go.

35:57.890 --> 35:59.389
Where is everybody?

35:59.458 --> 36:00.657
[Scott]: Hey!

36:02.361 --> 36:03.793
Oh, my goodness.

36:03.829 --> 36:05.295
I've missed you!

36:05.330 --> 36:06.596
You made it!

36:06.632 --> 36:08.131
Good.
Glad to have you.

36:09.535 --> 36:11.234
Emory!

36:11.270 --> 36:12.135
Come meet my mom.

36:12.171 --> 36:13.970
Hi!

36:14.006 --> 36:16.339
Emory Blake?
How nice to meet you.

36:16.375 --> 36:17.607
You too.

36:17.643 --> 36:19.254
I'm so happy
that you finally could make it.

36:19.278 --> 36:20.410
So am I.

36:20.445 --> 36:21.856
It has been
quite the adventure so far.

36:21.880 --> 36:23.180
I bet.

36:23.215 --> 36:24.014
I'm going to go help Hal
with the luggage.

36:24.049 --> 36:25.582
Okay.

36:25.617 --> 36:27.050
Did you see the Christmas tree?

36:27.085 --> 36:28.151
Tree?

36:28.187 --> 36:29.187
[Gasping]

36:31.523 --> 36:33.156
It's beautiful.

36:33.192 --> 36:34.624
Aw... mwah!

36:34.660 --> 36:36.560
Emory cut it down.

36:36.595 --> 36:37.595
Did she now?

36:37.629 --> 36:38.929
[Katy]:
She travels a lot.

36:38.964 --> 36:41.264
She's had Christmases
all around the world,

36:41.333 --> 36:43.066
but she hasn't had
a Christmas in America

36:43.135 --> 36:44.868
for a long time.

36:44.903 --> 36:46.436
Yeah, so long

36:46.471 --> 36:48.716
that I can't even remember
the last time I celebrated here.

36:48.740 --> 36:50.006
Well, then I'm so glad

36:50.075 --> 36:51.085
our family
could share it with you.

36:51.109 --> 36:53.076
I am going to talk Scott

36:53.111 --> 36:55.178
into making a roast
for Christmas dinner.

36:55.214 --> 36:56.580
Ooh, that sounds amazing,

36:56.648 --> 36:59.449
but I'm out of here
just as soon as my car is fixed.

36:59.484 --> 37:00.984
And when the bridge
is repaired.

37:01.019 --> 37:02.285
The bridge?

37:02.321 --> 37:03.453
It is out.

37:03.488 --> 37:04.666
That's why I brought
Marilyn up the back way,

37:04.690 --> 37:05.822
by ATV.

37:05.891 --> 37:06.823
Seriously?

37:06.892 --> 37:07.857
[Hal]:
They should have it fixed

37:07.893 --> 37:09.559
first thing
in the morning.

37:09.595 --> 37:10.660
[Sighing]

37:10.696 --> 37:12.862
That means
you get to stay here longer!

37:18.503 --> 37:19.436
[Scott]:
All right.

37:19.471 --> 37:20.604
Now, by show of hands,

37:20.639 --> 37:22.199
who wants to finish
decorating the tree?

37:22.941 --> 37:23.740
[Grunting]

37:23.775 --> 37:25.041
[Laughing]

37:27.813 --> 37:29.346
How come
they went out?

37:29.381 --> 37:30.480
Uh, one of them
must be out.

37:30.515 --> 37:32.282
Well, which one?

37:32.317 --> 37:33.661
You have to figure out
which one it is.

37:33.685 --> 37:35.285
Well, that's inefficient.

37:35.320 --> 37:37.988
Well, you wanted
a genuine Christmas experience.

37:38.023 --> 37:39.923
When do we get
to the cookies?

37:39.958 --> 37:41.358
Here's an extra.
Find it.

37:41.393 --> 37:42.393
Oh, here we go.

37:46.198 --> 37:47.597
Ha ha!

37:47.633 --> 37:49.266
[Cheering]

37:49.301 --> 37:53.637
