♪ Your leaves
are so unchanging ♪

38:25.103 --> 38:26.670
Looking good!

38:27.939 --> 38:30.707
[Katy]:
Oh, what are those?

38:30.742 --> 38:32.086
[Marilyn]: I brought these
from home.

38:32.110 --> 38:33.454
These are your
Christmas ornaments.

38:33.478 --> 38:36.579
I've had them in
storage in the attic.

38:37.883 --> 38:39.260
I think it's time
we bring them out.

38:39.284 --> 38:40.284
Don't you?

38:44.723 --> 38:47.157
Now, this one...

38:48.927 --> 38:50.093
This one has
your name on it.

39:00.672 --> 39:01.604
Your mom and I made that

39:01.640 --> 39:03.306
for your first Christmas.

39:15.520 --> 39:16.853
What do you guys think

39:16.888 --> 39:18.800
about putting some of these
on the Christmas tree?

39:18.824 --> 39:19.923
Candy canes?

39:19.958 --> 39:22.392
One of my first
Christmas memories

39:22.427 --> 39:23.793
was one of our neighbors
in Berlin,

39:23.829 --> 39:26.896
their tree was just...
Covered in them.

39:26.932 --> 39:28.732
It was so festive.

39:28.767 --> 39:30.734
So you do have
a Christmas tradition

39:30.802 --> 39:32.001
after all.

39:33.372 --> 39:34.871
I guess so.

39:34.906 --> 39:35.839
Hadn't thought of it
like that.

39:35.907 --> 39:37.941
I love that idea.

39:37.976 --> 39:38.942
All right, we've got
to make sure

39:38.977 --> 39:40.054
we get them all
on the tree.

39:40.078 --> 39:41.277
All of them?

39:41.346 --> 39:42.379
Where's the fun in that?

39:43.415 --> 39:44.881
Here you go.

39:44.916 --> 39:46.015
[Katy]:
So pretty!

39:46.051 --> 39:48.318
Yeah!

39:54.259 --> 39:55.291
What's up?

39:55.360 --> 39:57.327
How do you put pictures
onto a computer?

39:57.362 --> 39:58.661
Oh, you've got to plug it in.

39:58.697 --> 40:00.663
There's a cord
in the back of the case.

40:00.699 --> 40:01.664
Like a phone.

40:01.700 --> 40:02.832
Yeah, like a phone.

40:02.868 --> 40:04.000
Thanks.

40:04.035 --> 40:06.970
I have an idea
for a project with photos.

40:07.005 --> 40:08.338
What about?

40:08.373 --> 40:10.573
I can't tell you.
It's a surprise.

40:12.844 --> 40:13.743
[Phone chiming]

40:13.779 --> 40:14.878
Oh...

40:14.913 --> 40:16.079
What?
What's wrong?

40:16.148 --> 40:17.514
Uh, nothing.
It's from Alice.

40:17.549 --> 40:19.048
I lost track of time.

40:19.117 --> 40:21.484
Katy, we have to get ready
for "the nutcracker."

40:21.520 --> 40:22.986
What about the tree?

40:23.054 --> 40:24.198
We're going to have
to finish it tomorrow.

40:24.222 --> 40:25.533
Alice and Johnny will
be here in 15 minutes.

40:25.557 --> 40:26.557
We've got to get ready.

40:26.591 --> 40:27.824
Go, go, go, go,
go, go, go, go.

40:30.629 --> 40:32.162
We won't stay out too long.

40:32.197 --> 40:33.341
[Marilyn]:
Don't worry about us.

40:33.365 --> 40:35.165
I have plenty of wrapping to do.

40:35.200 --> 40:36.200
Ooh, I'll help.

40:38.236 --> 40:40.370
[Marilyn]:
Well, thank you.

40:40.405 --> 40:42.038
Have fun on your date.

40:43.508 --> 40:44.741
Not a date.

40:51.683 --> 40:53.082
[Sighing]

40:53.118 --> 40:54.128
I haven't wrapped
this many presents

40:54.152 --> 40:55.485
since I spent a semester

40:55.554 --> 40:57.954
with the Marcoux family
in Belgium...

40:58.023 --> 40:59.656
All eleven of them.

40:59.691 --> 41:00.824
Oh, my.

41:00.859 --> 41:02.358
[Laughing]

41:02.394 --> 41:04.794
And what about your parents.
Do they celebrate?

41:04.830 --> 41:06.996
Yeah, they do...

41:07.065 --> 41:08.331
Just from, you know,

41:08.400 --> 41:10.867
wherever we are
in the world,

41:10.902 --> 41:12.013
which isn't usually
the states.

41:12.037 --> 41:14.170
When Scott was growing up,

41:14.206 --> 41:16.639
Christmas was our
favorite time of year.

41:16.675 --> 41:18.608
I would cook for days.

41:18.643 --> 41:20.910
We would roast
chestnuts,

41:20.946 --> 41:23.090
and I would make sure the house
was thoroughly decorated,

41:23.114 --> 41:24.647
of course.

41:26.251 --> 41:29.052
We haven't done that
in years...

41:29.087 --> 41:30.487
Not since...

41:33.391 --> 41:34.691
That must've been so hard.

41:34.759 --> 41:37.827
Yeah, it was.

41:37.896 --> 41:41.030
Scott just seems
a little lost ever since.

41:41.066 --> 41:42.431
No, that's not
the right word.

41:42.533 --> 41:43.533
It's more, um...

41:43.568 --> 41:44.934
Protective...

41:45.003 --> 41:46.536
Of Katy and himself.

41:46.571 --> 41:48.538
That's understandable.

41:48.573 --> 41:50.039
But it's not sustainable.

41:50.108 --> 41:54.377
He used to be
so much more... free.

41:54.412 --> 41:56.312
I just want him
to get back to that,

41:56.381 --> 41:59.015
be a bit more open.

41:59.050 --> 42:01.150
Well...
Maybe he'll meet someone.

42:17.202 --> 42:18.202
More tea?

42:19.204 --> 42:21.004
Sure.
Thank you.

42:28.079 --> 42:29.712
[Car approaching]

42:33.852 --> 42:35.018
[Car doors closing]

42:35.053 --> 42:36.286
[Alice]: That was so much fun.

42:37.989 --> 42:39.389
Good night.

42:45.864 --> 42:47.397
Bye!

42:47.465 --> 42:49.299
Okay, have
a good night!

42:56.074 --> 42:57.707
Hey!
How was it?

42:57.742 --> 42:59.776
So much fun.

42:59.844 --> 43:01.978
Oh...
Aren't you tired?

43:02.013 --> 43:04.147
Not me.

43:04.182 --> 43:05.448
Oh...
[Laughing]

43:06.585 --> 43:07.784
Uh, hey, um...

43:07.819 --> 43:09.586
The garage called,

43:09.621 --> 43:10.898
and they're going
to bring my car by here

43:10.922 --> 43:11.821
tomorrow afternoon.

43:11.890 --> 43:13.890
So you're leaving?

43:13.925 --> 43:14.891
No!

43:14.926 --> 43:15.992
Katy...

43:16.027 --> 43:17.107
But she's going
to be alone.

43:20.298 --> 43:21.309
Wouldn't be my first time.

43:21.333 --> 43:22.699
[Marilyn]: Stay.

43:22.767 --> 43:24.667
I mean,
you're clearly having fun.

43:26.271 --> 43:28.871
The company
has made it wonderful.

43:28.907 --> 43:30.673
Then keep the company.

43:30.709 --> 43:31.808
[Laughing]

43:31.843 --> 43:33.209
Dad?

43:40.285 --> 43:41.285
It's up to Emory.

43:47.359 --> 43:49.292
As long as
I get my article done,

43:49.327 --> 43:51.027
I don't suppose it could hurt.

43:51.096 --> 43:52.261
Yes!

43:52.297 --> 43:53.297
Yes!

43:53.331 --> 43:54.731
Great.

44:02.273 --> 44:03.840
How goes the article?

44:03.908 --> 44:05.908
Slowly,
but at least it's going.

44:05.944 --> 44:06.976
What about you?

44:07.045 --> 44:07.877
You got some work
waiting for you

44:07.912 --> 44:08.945
when you get home?

44:09.014 --> 44:10.747
Plenty when all
is said and done.

44:10.815 --> 44:12.715
Uh, corporate law?

44:12.751 --> 44:13.850
Good guess...

44:13.885 --> 44:14.984
Thank you.

44:15.020 --> 44:16.686
But wrong.

44:16.755 --> 44:18.454
Uh, good guess once.

44:18.490 --> 44:20.223
Oh, so you once did
corporate law.

44:20.258 --> 44:21.324
Once.

44:21.393 --> 44:23.393
I worked every single
minute I could

44:23.428 --> 44:24.360
and far more
than I should.

44:24.396 --> 44:26.162
What happened?

44:26.197 --> 44:27.697
Lisa.

44:27.732 --> 44:28.898
You know,
she always begged me

44:28.967 --> 44:30.199
to work fewer hours,

44:30.268 --> 44:32.969
and I...
Never listened,

44:33.004 --> 44:34.771
and after she was gone,
everything shifted.

44:36.708 --> 44:38.041
After you.

44:42.414 --> 44:43.780
All right, so...

44:43.815 --> 44:45.448
What can we do to make

44:45.483 --> 44:46.927
the most amazing
gingerbread house ever?

44:46.951 --> 44:48.351
An ice rink in the back yard!

44:48.420 --> 44:49.552
Mm!

44:49.587 --> 44:50.953
Yes!

44:50.989 --> 44:51.989
I'll make blue frosting.

44:52.057 --> 44:53.022
Perfect...
I think we need

44:53.058 --> 44:54.458
a fallen ice skater
on the ice, too.

44:54.526 --> 44:55.591
Just for
authenticity.

44:55.660 --> 44:56.592
That's mean.

44:56.661 --> 44:57.794
[Giggling]

44:57.829 --> 44:59.896
Okay,
what else?

44:59.964 --> 45:01.531
We need pine trees.

45:01.599 --> 45:05.068
We can use pretzel sticks
with dyed green rice krispies

45:05.103 --> 45:06.113
or popcorn for the leaves.

45:06.137 --> 45:07.303
If all else fails,

45:07.372 --> 45:08.416
we can just use
an overturned sugar cone

45:08.440 --> 45:09.440
with green gum drops.

45:09.507 --> 45:11.441
How do you know all this?

45:11.509 --> 45:13.543
We lived next to a bakery
when I lived in London.

45:13.578 --> 45:14.855
You'll find I'm a wealth
of trivial information

45:14.879 --> 45:15.845
like that.

45:15.880 --> 45:17.613
As I'm learning.

45:17.649 --> 45:19.415
What about the roof?

45:19.451 --> 45:20.283
Oh, I know, why don't we use
Graham crackers?

45:20.318 --> 45:21.451
Or brown frosting,

45:21.486 --> 45:23.453
or we could even use
some almonds, you know,

45:23.521 --> 45:25.121
as shingles.

45:25.190 --> 45:26.190
Not almonds.

45:27.392 --> 45:29.158
Why?

45:29.194 --> 45:30.293
It's a long story.

45:34.132 --> 45:36.052
Are you familiar with
Swedish Christmas porridge?

45:37.202 --> 45:38.301
No.

45:38.369 --> 45:40.236
Let's just say
I'm recently single

45:40.271 --> 45:41.671
because of it.

45:42.807 --> 45:44.140
Interesting.

45:50.014 --> 45:51.280
We could use
white frosting

45:51.316 --> 45:53.583
and put snow
all around it.

45:53.618 --> 45:54.584
What do you think?

45:54.619 --> 45:55.551
Perfect!
I love it.

45:55.587 --> 45:56.853
Snow everywhere.

45:56.888 --> 45:57.920
Everywhere.

46:04.329 --> 46:05.561
Finishing touch.

46:05.597 --> 46:06.896
Mm-hmm.

46:07.899 --> 46:09.532
That's a good look
for your snowman,

46:09.567 --> 46:11.145
but you need to go get yourself
a new hat,

46:11.169 --> 46:12.346
'cause your snowman
is presently warmer

46:12.370 --> 46:13.569
than you are.

46:13.638 --> 46:14.904
No colds for Christmas.

46:14.973 --> 46:16.339
Picture time!

46:19.010 --> 46:21.444
Say... snowflakes.

46:21.479 --> 46:23.412
Snowflakes!

46:23.448 --> 46:24.680
[Camera clicking]

46:25.950 --> 46:27.083
Can I take
my camera

46:27.152 --> 46:28.684
to Johnny's party?

46:28.720 --> 46:29.786
Of course.

46:29.821 --> 46:31.487
I'll go get my hat.

46:31.523 --> 46:32.955
Party?

46:32.991 --> 46:34.123
Yeah, uh...

46:34.159 --> 46:35.169
Alice apparently
throws a party

46:35.193 --> 46:37.593
for all the families
that are in town.

46:37.629 --> 46:39.529
She made sure
to invite you and my mom.

46:39.564 --> 46:40.696
That's nice of her.

46:40.732 --> 46:43.065
She's a nice person.

46:43.101 --> 46:44.367
I take it
your date went well?

46:45.904 --> 46:47.203
I'm sorry.
I'll stop.

46:47.272 --> 46:48.272
I'll stop.

46:48.306 --> 46:50.139
So, you're currently single.

46:50.175 --> 46:51.240
Is that why you came

46:51.276 --> 46:53.543
to spend time alone
for Christmas?

46:53.578 --> 46:54.644
A bit.

46:54.679 --> 46:55.878
I guess I came out here

46:55.914 --> 46:57.747
just to, you know,
gather my thoughts

46:57.816 --> 47:00.383
and why I...

47:00.451 --> 47:02.652
I don't know,
haven't settled down...

47:02.687 --> 47:04.987
And then my editor
took advantage

47:05.023 --> 47:06.289
of my quiet alone time.

47:06.324 --> 47:07.957
And then we barged in.

47:07.992 --> 47:09.892
Which has proven to be helpful.

47:09.928 --> 47:11.294
Glad to be of service.

47:11.329 --> 47:12.228
Yeah, it's been...

47:12.263 --> 47:13.663
Different...

47:13.698 --> 47:16.065
Actually doing all these things,
you know?

47:16.134 --> 47:17.533
Decorating the tree...

47:17.602 --> 47:19.468
building this girl here.

47:19.504 --> 47:20.937
[Laughing]

47:20.972 --> 47:23.139
I didn't realize
how much I'd been missing.

47:25.844 --> 47:28.044
Now I just need to figure out
the angle of this article.

47:29.147 --> 47:31.113
Yeah, so,
back to this almond thing,

47:31.149 --> 47:32.815
how did that play
into you being single?

47:34.352 --> 47:36.886
To be fair, it wasn't entirely
the almond's fault.

47:36.921 --> 47:38.788
The break-up was inevitable.

47:38.823 --> 47:40.289
Why?

47:40.358 --> 47:42.859
Well, for starters,
we weren't together enough.

47:42.894 --> 47:44.260
Because of your travels?

47:45.630 --> 47:46.841
Yeah, that was definitely
an issue,

47:46.865 --> 47:48.264
but...

47:50.902 --> 47:52.835
Let's just say
something was missing.

48:03.314 --> 48:04.213
Hello.

48:04.249 --> 48:06.282
Hello!

48:06.317 --> 48:07.561
Oh, I'm so glad
you all could make it.

48:07.585 --> 48:09.285
Great dress, Emory.

48:09.320 --> 48:11.087
Thank you.
You too.

48:11.122 --> 48:12.588
Thanks.

48:12.657 --> 48:13.923
Katy, Johnny's upstairs,

48:13.992 --> 48:15.469
making Christmas ornaments
with the other children,

48:15.493 --> 48:16.392
if you'd like to join.

48:16.461 --> 48:17.660
Can I, dad?

48:17.695 --> 48:18.961
Absolutely.

48:21.132 --> 48:22.398
Um, so,

48:22.433 --> 48:24.200
help yourselves
to everything.

48:24.235 --> 48:27.503
I'm just going to steal Scott
for a minute.

48:29.340 --> 48:30.573
I have some
attorney friends

48:30.642 --> 48:32.441
that I would like
for you to meet.

48:32.477 --> 48:34.710
Great.

48:34.779 --> 48:36.646
She is so lovely.

48:36.681 --> 48:38.381
And smooth.

48:38.416 --> 48:39.615
So smooth.

48:39.651 --> 48:40.917
Eggnog?

48:40.952 --> 48:42.251
So yes.

48:42.287 --> 48:43.386
[Hal]:
Hey, Marilyn!

48:43.421 --> 48:44.531
Oh, look who's here.
Look, I'll be back.

48:44.555 --> 48:45.655
Yeah.

48:45.690 --> 48:47.156
Come meet
the travel group.

49:24.062 --> 49:26.128
Ah, fancy meeting Hal here.

49:26.197 --> 49:27.263
What a surprise!

49:27.298 --> 49:28.831
[Chuckling]

49:28.866 --> 49:31.500
It was a very interesting
conversation.

49:31.536 --> 49:32.868
Hmm?

49:32.904 --> 49:35.805
They are all members
of the pine grove globetrotters,

49:35.840 --> 49:37.673
and they have invited me
to join them

49:37.742 --> 49:39.575
on their upcoming trip
down the Danube.

49:39.610 --> 49:40.610
That is awesome!

49:42.113 --> 49:43.446
I don't really
travel...

49:43.514 --> 49:44.413
Well, not anymore.

49:44.449 --> 49:46.549
Why not?

49:46.584 --> 49:47.616
Well, when
I was younger,

49:47.652 --> 49:48.517
I had to raise Scott,

49:48.553 --> 49:50.252
and then...

49:50.288 --> 49:52.021
I think I just got
comfortable, you know,

49:52.090 --> 49:53.489
or maybe stuck.

49:53.558 --> 49:55.591
Gosh, I can't imagine
not traveling.

49:55.626 --> 49:56.592
Really?

49:56.627 --> 49:57.693
Yeah.

49:57.729 --> 49:58.729
Well, aren't we a pair.

49:59.731 --> 50:00.731
[Clinking]

50:03.568 --> 50:04.467
Do you want one?

50:04.502 --> 50:06.602
Mm-hmm.

50:10.641 --> 50:11.941
You want to hear a crazy idea

50:11.976 --> 50:13.554
about what would make me
very happy right now?

50:13.578 --> 50:15.845
What?

50:15.880 --> 50:18.714
Going home...
Making tea...

50:18.783 --> 50:21.417
Working on our
gingerbread house.

50:21.452 --> 50:22.985
Okay,
so it's not just me,

50:23.021 --> 50:24.220
because I have been thinking

50:24.255 --> 50:26.689
about using a chocolate bar
for a front door

50:26.724 --> 50:27.724
all night!

50:27.759 --> 50:29.325
Gingerbread nerd.

50:29.360 --> 50:30.371
I just think
you're jealous

50:30.395 --> 50:32.862
that you didn't think
of it first.

50:32.897 --> 50:34.230
Guilty.

50:34.298 --> 50:35.498
All right,
I'll get the girls.

50:35.533 --> 50:36.766
I'll get the coats.

51:02.493 --> 51:04.293
♪ Christmas is near ♪

51:04.328 --> 51:07.630
♪ Christmas is just
round the corner ♪

51:07.665 --> 51:09.398
[♪♪♪]

51:09.434 --> 51:11.133
♪ He's almost here ♪

51:11.202 --> 51:14.370
♪ Santa, he won't be
much longer ♪

51:14.405 --> 51:16.105
[♪♪♪]

51:16.174 --> 51:17.640
♪ So bring on the cheer ♪

51:17.675 --> 51:21.143
♪ 'Cause Christmas
is just round the corner ♪

51:21.179 --> 51:23.079
[♪♪♪]

51:23.114 --> 51:25.047
♪ Counting his days ♪

51:25.083 --> 51:27.783
♪ Santa, he just takes forever ♪

51:27.852 --> 51:29.752
[♪♪♪]

51:29.787 --> 51:31.220
♪ Watch for his sleigh ♪

51:31.255 --> 51:34.190
♪ His reindeers
will all be together ♪

51:34.225 --> 51:36.459
[♪♪♪]

51:36.494 --> 51:37.860
♪ 'Cause Christmas is near ♪

51:37.929 --> 51:41.097
♪ It's just round the corner ♪

51:41.132 --> 51:43.232
[♪♪♪]

51:43.267 --> 51:44.900
♪ Get out the tree ♪

51:44.936 --> 51:46.569
♪ Put up the lights... ♪

52:02.487 --> 52:03.886
Do any of them
have an ice rink.

52:03.955 --> 52:05.488
Oh, no, no, no,
just ours,

52:05.523 --> 52:07.823
and our gumdrop trees
are the best.

52:07.859 --> 52:09.325
Yeah!
[Laughing]

52:09.393 --> 52:11.093
[MC]:
All right.

52:11.129 --> 52:13.395
There were
some wonderful entries,

52:13.431 --> 52:15.865
and like last year,

52:15.900 --> 52:18.501
this year's decision
is unanimous.

52:18.536 --> 52:20.469
Okay, let's cross our fingers.

52:20.505 --> 52:21.971
Fingers.

52:22.006 --> 52:23.283
For evoking the feeling of being
at home during Christmas,

52:23.307 --> 52:26.609
the winner is...

52:26.644 --> 52:27.710
Number 12!

52:27.745 --> 52:29.945
[Clapping]

52:30.014 --> 52:31.714
[Laughing]

52:38.990 --> 52:39.922
Oh, my gosh!

52:39.957 --> 52:40.957
Thank you.

52:44.195 --> 52:45.494
Thank you.

52:45.530 --> 52:47.050
Let's get a shot
of the winning family.

52:50.201 --> 52:51.201
Hey.

52:54.939 --> 52:56.338
No, no.
Do a family...

53:07.018 --> 53:09.285
[Typing]

53:21.032 --> 53:25.334
[♪♪♪]

53:31.209 --> 53:33.542
I'm so proud
of you, sweetheart.

53:33.578 --> 53:35.010
We did it together.

53:35.046 --> 53:36.445
Yeah,
but without your suggestion,

53:36.480 --> 53:37.658
we'd still be in San Francisco

53:37.682 --> 53:39.515
instead of snuggling trophies.

53:40.785 --> 53:41.984
Can we come here
next year?

53:44.121 --> 53:45.788
You bet.

53:45.856 --> 53:47.556
Can we invite Emory?

53:47.592 --> 53:49.325
Ah...

53:51.629 --> 53:52.906
Yeah, I doubt that's going
to happen, sweetheart.

53:52.930 --> 53:54.029
Why?

53:54.098 --> 53:55.464
She's been
a part of everything,

53:55.499 --> 53:57.433
and a big part
of why this is so much fun.

53:58.736 --> 54:00.135
It's true.

54:00.204 --> 54:03.239
She is
an unexpected plus,

54:03.274 --> 54:04.673
but you know,
she has her own life,

54:04.709 --> 54:06.075
a very full life,

54:06.110 --> 54:07.854
which I'm sure will take her
someplace else next year.

54:07.878 --> 54:09.345
We can still ask her.

54:11.949 --> 54:13.749
Get some rest.

54:25.496 --> 54:26.895
Katy sleeping?

54:26.931 --> 54:29.632
Yeah,
the sleep of the victorious.

54:29.700 --> 54:31.567
[Chuckling]

54:31.602 --> 54:32.835
She asked

54:32.870 --> 54:34.870
if we could come back
here again next year.

54:34.905 --> 54:36.405
Oh, well,

54:36.474 --> 54:37.484
I think I'd
like that, too.

54:37.508 --> 54:38.874
Yeah?

54:38.943 --> 54:40.976
Yeah.
It's been nice.

54:41.012 --> 54:43.779
Are you enjoying being
out of your comfort zone?

54:43.814 --> 54:47.349
Yes, I am, smarty.

54:47.385 --> 54:49.151
Hal, um...

54:49.186 --> 54:51.854
Asked me to join
the local travel group.

54:51.889 --> 54:54.023
They're doing a riverboat tour
down the Danube.

54:54.091 --> 54:55.958
Wow.

54:57.561 --> 54:58.627
And?

54:58.663 --> 55:00.429
I just don't think
it's me.

55:00.464 --> 55:01.897
Oh, but it could be, though.

55:01.932 --> 55:03.599
I suppose it could.

55:03.668 --> 55:06.402
Go!
Travel the world.

55:06.470 --> 55:07.269
Branch out.

55:07.305 --> 55:09.204
Well, at the very least,

55:09.273 --> 55:12.107
I'm going to have Hal reserve
this cabin for us next year,

55:12.143 --> 55:15.077
exclusively,
this time.

55:17.214 --> 55:20.049
Katy did ask
if we could invite Emory.

55:20.084 --> 55:23.018
Well, I don't suppose
it would hurt to ask.

55:23.054 --> 55:25.587
That's exactly what she said.

55:25.623 --> 55:27.256
Exactly...

55:29.160 --> 55:30.292
Except it kind of does.

55:30.361 --> 55:32.027
Why?

55:33.698 --> 55:34.908
Mom, she's not going
to say yes.

55:34.932 --> 55:36.865
How do you know that?

55:36.901 --> 55:38.834
Mom, Emory is a bright
and independent woman

55:38.869 --> 55:40.269
who's traveled the world.

55:40.304 --> 55:41.670
She's not looking
to settle down,

55:41.739 --> 55:42.783
and she's not looking to spend
next Christmas here again

55:42.807 --> 55:44.139
at pine grove.

55:44.208 --> 55:47.776
She's spending this Christmas
with us in pine grove.

55:47.845 --> 55:51.046
Look, the roads are clear.
The bridge is open.

55:51.082 --> 55:52.815
She decided to stay.

55:52.850 --> 55:55.317
Yeah,
but that's this Christmas.

55:55.353 --> 55:56.930
You know, it's sort of fun
and spontaneous,

55:56.954 --> 55:58.220
and another one of her stories

55:58.255 --> 56:00.155
that she'll be able
to share sometime...

56:00.191 --> 56:01.690
In the future,

56:01.726 --> 56:02.869
to someone else
she meets along the way.

56:02.893 --> 56:04.693
Mm.

56:04.729 --> 56:06.169
I think the one
creating the stories,

56:06.197 --> 56:08.831
my darling son...

56:08.866 --> 56:10.132
Is you.

56:34.058 --> 56:35.924
Where's Orion?

56:35.993 --> 56:38.494
Um, right...
There.

56:40.164 --> 56:41.308
[Scott]:
As pretty as that is,

56:41.332 --> 56:43.732
this isn't a catamaran
in the Caribbean.

56:43.768 --> 56:45.434
I would advise sleeping
indoors tonight.

56:45.469 --> 56:46.902
It is cold.

56:46.937 --> 56:48.737
Yeah, I noticed.

56:48.773 --> 56:50.806
Fortunately,
I have a fireplace

56:50.841 --> 56:52.975
I get to snuggle up
next to,

56:53.010 --> 56:53.942
get some more
writing done.

56:53.978 --> 56:55.544
Oh, you finally
figured it out?

56:55.613 --> 56:57.012
Yes.

56:57.081 --> 56:58.280
The hard part now

56:58.315 --> 57:00.883
is keeping it
under 2,000 words.

57:00.918 --> 57:02.851
That's good news,
isn't it?

57:02.887 --> 57:05.020
Yeah, it is...

57:05.055 --> 57:07.156
For the article,

57:07.191 --> 57:08.191
and for this book idea

57:08.225 --> 57:09.691
that I've been
flirting with

57:09.727 --> 57:11.627
for the last couple years.

57:11.662 --> 57:13.262
Oh, well, now
I'm intrigued.

57:13.297 --> 57:14.830
Mm...

57:14.899 --> 57:16.231
You can read it
when it's done.

57:22.306 --> 57:24.339
How's it feel?

57:24.375 --> 57:25.375
To get it going again?

57:27.611 --> 57:28.811
Good...

57:30.047 --> 57:31.224
You know, which isn't
always the case

57:31.248 --> 57:32.281
with writing.

57:32.349 --> 57:34.082
Well, it hasn't been
for me lately.

57:34.118 --> 57:35.717
Really?
I thought...

57:35.753 --> 57:36.718
I thought you loved it.

57:36.754 --> 57:39.455
I do...

57:39.490 --> 57:40.856
But lately, I've been thinking

57:40.925 --> 57:43.892
about, you know, taking a break
from so much traveling

57:43.928 --> 57:48.464
and just...
Focusing on the book.

57:49.500 --> 57:51.033
That's funny.

57:51.068 --> 57:52.367
What?

57:52.403 --> 57:55.604
Recently, I've been thinking
the exact opposite...

57:55.639 --> 57:57.339
How now,
Katy's getting older

57:57.408 --> 58:00.142
and how she can appreciate
going out and seeing the world.

58:00.211 --> 58:02.211
She's so curious.

58:02.246 --> 58:03.579
That's important,
you know.

58:03.614 --> 58:05.047
It's how we grow.

58:05.082 --> 58:07.382
Yeah.

58:07.418 --> 58:11.520
I feel like I forgot
how to be curious, you know.

58:11.589 --> 58:13.088
I forgot
how to be open.

58:13.123 --> 58:15.257
I feel like I've
been locked up...

58:15.292 --> 58:16.892
A lot.

58:18.095 --> 58:21.396
When Katy suggested
we come here,

58:21.432 --> 58:25.100
my first instinct was to say no,

58:25.135 --> 58:26.635
and that never used to be me.

58:29.573 --> 58:31.907
Well, I'm glad you said yes.

58:35.079 --> 58:36.079
Yeah?

58:37.214 --> 58:38.214
Yeah.

58:40.284 --> 58:41.850
I wouldn't have
met you otherwise.

58:55.165 --> 58:57.633
[Katy]: Dad, can I have
some water, please?

59:06.277 --> 59:07.277
I should probably...

59:10.648 --> 59:12.948
Yeah,
I'm right behind you.

59:16.954 --> 59:19.555
Don't forget to come
in from the cold.

59:19.590 --> 59:20.722
Coming, sweetheart.

59:34.872 --> 59:35.872
[Mail whooshing]

59:38.842 --> 59:40.108
[Computer chiming]

59:55.960 --> 59:57.659
[Phone ringing]

01:00:00.130 --> 01:00:02.030
Emory?
Is everything okay?

01:00:02.066 --> 01:00:04.199
Everything's fine.

01:00:04.234 --> 01:00:07.169
I just finished my article,
and I just wanted to say hello.

01:00:07.204 --> 01:00:10.305
Well, in that case,
congratulations and hello.

01:00:10.341 --> 01:00:11.406
<i>How's pine grove?</i>

01:00:11.442 --> 01:00:14.076
Oh, it's just beautiful.

01:00:14.111 --> 01:00:15.221
Oh, and remember
how I emailed you

01:00:15.245 --> 01:00:16.545
about the whole cabin mix-up?

01:00:16.580 --> 01:00:17.913
Yeah?

01:00:17.982 --> 01:00:21.350
<i>Well, I actually ended up
staying with the family,</i>

01:00:21.385 --> 01:00:22.918
and we've been going around,

01:00:22.953 --> 01:00:25.354
doing as many old-fashioned
Christmas traditions and things

01:00:25.422 --> 01:00:26.488
we can think of,

01:00:26.557 --> 01:00:29.291
and it's just been... magic.

01:00:29.360 --> 01:00:31.526
Christmas magic?

01:00:31.562 --> 01:00:32.527
<i>Yeah...</i>

01:00:32.563 --> 01:00:35.197
Christmas magic...

01:00:35.232 --> 01:00:37.265
And it, um...

01:00:37.301 --> 01:00:38.500
It got me thinking.

01:00:38.535 --> 01:00:39.735
Yeah, what about?

01:00:39.770 --> 01:00:42.304
Traditions.

01:00:42.339 --> 01:00:43.850
Why don't we have
any Christmas traditions?

01:00:43.874 --> 01:00:45.707
But we do.

01:00:45.743 --> 01:00:47.075
We do?

01:00:47.111 --> 01:00:48.111
<i>Sure.</i>

01:00:48.145 --> 01:00:49.478
For both your mom and me,

01:00:49.513 --> 01:00:50.779
the most important tradition

01:00:50.814 --> 01:00:52.781
was that we're always together
for Christmas.

01:00:52.816 --> 01:00:55.117
No matter where in the world
we were,

01:00:55.152 --> 01:00:57.252
it was always the three of us,
side-by-side.

01:00:57.287 --> 01:00:58.420
Yeah.

01:00:59.857 --> 01:01:01.356
The three musketeers.

01:01:01.392 --> 01:01:03.091
Exactly.

01:01:03.160 --> 01:01:04.960
But we aren't anymore.

01:01:04.995 --> 01:01:07.029
<i>Well, we always invite you
to join us,</i>

01:01:07.064 --> 01:01:08.330
<i>but, uh...</i>

01:01:08.365 --> 01:01:11.233
You've got your own life
to lead now, Emory,

01:01:11.268 --> 01:01:12.501
and I'm proud of you
for that.

01:01:15.105 --> 01:01:16.204
Dad?

01:01:16.240 --> 01:01:17.906
Yeah?
What is it, sweetie?

01:01:17.941 --> 01:01:19.307
Can we make sure

01:01:19.343 --> 01:01:21.343
the three of us are together
next Christmas?

01:01:21.378 --> 01:01:22.878
Maybe come up here
to pine grove?

01:01:22.946 --> 01:01:24.413
I'd like that.

01:01:24.448 --> 01:01:26.281
I think that's a great idea.

01:01:30.054 --> 01:01:31.654
[Whistling
we wish you a merry Christmas]

01:01:34.925 --> 01:01:35.925
Whatcha doing there?

01:01:35.959 --> 01:01:38.060
Making a stocking
for Emory.

01:01:38.095 --> 01:01:39.628
It's not as pretty as ours,
but...

01:01:39.663 --> 01:01:40.829
She'll love it.

01:01:42.966 --> 01:01:45.100
Do you think we'll see her
after Christmas?

01:01:48.739 --> 01:01:49.838
Morning.

01:01:49.873 --> 01:01:50.873
Morning.

01:01:50.908 --> 01:01:52.307
[Marilyn]:
According to Hal,

01:01:52.342 --> 01:01:54.376
there is a Christmas
hay ride tonight.

01:01:54.445 --> 01:01:55.510
They're getting it in

01:01:55.579 --> 01:01:57.546
before the big
snow storm tomorrow.

01:01:57.581 --> 01:01:58.647
I want to go
on a hay ride.

01:01:58.716 --> 01:01:59.981
Is it on the list?

01:02:00.050 --> 01:02:02.617
It is now.
Number eight.

01:02:02.686 --> 01:02:03.686
[Laughing]

01:02:07.891 --> 01:02:08.924
You, uh, want to join us?

01:02:11.495 --> 01:02:13.495
Sure, I'm game.

01:02:15.065 --> 01:02:18.100
[People]:
♪ fa la la la la la la la la ♪

01:02:18.168 --> 01:02:21.002
♪ Don we now our gay apparel ♪

01:02:21.038 --> 01:02:24.439
♪ Fa la la la la la la la la ♪

01:02:27.411 --> 01:02:29.411
Very important
s'mores question...

01:02:29.446 --> 01:02:30.446
Mm?

01:02:30.481 --> 01:02:31.847
The marshmallow.

01:02:31.882 --> 01:02:34.182
Do you scorch,
slow roast,

01:02:34.218 --> 01:02:36.551
or, please say no...
Leave it uncooked?

01:02:36.620 --> 01:02:37.819
Okay, don't think
I'm weird,

01:02:37.855 --> 01:02:40.489
but I've never
actually had a s'more.

01:02:40.524 --> 01:02:41.524
Say what?

01:02:41.592 --> 01:02:42.457
[Laughing]

01:02:42.493 --> 01:02:44.726
Wow.

01:02:44.762 --> 01:02:46.372
All right, well,
that is soon to be rectified.

01:02:46.396 --> 01:02:47.462
Good.

01:02:47.531 --> 01:02:49.231
And by the way,
the answer is slow roast.

01:02:49.266 --> 01:02:50.966
Ah, slow roast.

01:02:51.001 --> 01:02:52.501
Filed away.

01:02:52.536 --> 01:02:53.813
I'll be back
with the ingredients.

01:02:53.837 --> 01:02:55.670
Okay.

01:02:57.174 --> 01:02:58.740
Say cheese!

01:02:58.776 --> 01:03:00.108
Cheese.

01:03:00.144 --> 01:03:01.109
[Camera clicking]

01:03:01.145 --> 01:03:02.155
Is this for your photo project?

01:03:02.179 --> 01:03:03.245
Yep.

01:03:03.280 --> 01:03:05.347
Mm.
When do I get to see it?

01:03:05.382 --> 01:03:07.015
When it's ready.
Are you having fun?

01:03:07.050 --> 01:03:09.484
I am.

01:03:09.520 --> 01:03:10.630
You know, I haven't been
to a Christmas bonfire

01:03:10.654 --> 01:03:11.654
in...

01:03:12.956 --> 01:03:14.289
I don't even know.

01:03:14.324 --> 01:03:15.457
It doesn't matter.

01:03:15.492 --> 01:03:18.260
I'm at this bonfire,
and I am having fun.

01:03:18.295 --> 01:03:19.528
[Johnny]: Katy!

01:03:20.531 --> 01:03:22.130
See you!

01:03:25.669 --> 01:03:27.435
So, was I right,
or was I right?

01:03:27.471 --> 01:03:29.371
Oh, man, you were
definitely right.

01:03:29.406 --> 01:03:31.126
This place has made
Christmas special again.

01:03:33.911 --> 01:03:36.478
And, um...
Emory, is she having fun?

01:03:38.315 --> 01:03:39.281
I think so.

01:03:39.316 --> 01:03:40.482
I'm glad.

01:03:42.486 --> 01:03:44.252
Come on, you'd have to be blind

01:03:44.288 --> 01:03:46.099
not to see the chemistry
between the two of you,

01:03:46.123 --> 01:03:47.834
and I'm not interested
in chasing after someone

01:03:47.858 --> 01:03:50.592
who's falling for someone else.

01:03:52.863 --> 01:03:54.963
Yeah, it just...

01:03:54.998 --> 01:03:57.432
It just happened
out of the blue.

01:03:57.467 --> 01:03:58.600
I mean, it's crazy.

01:03:59.770 --> 01:04:01.036
Enjoy it.

01:04:04.575 --> 01:04:06.508
You know, not everyone
gets that kind of magic.

01:04:08.812 --> 01:04:09.812
Thank you.

01:04:09.847 --> 01:04:11.146
Merry Christmas.

01:04:11.181 --> 01:04:12.514
Merry Christmas.

01:04:18.789 --> 01:04:20.322
[Phone ringing]

01:04:22.025 --> 01:04:23.124
Hey.

01:04:23.160 --> 01:04:24.025
Help. I'm spinning.

01:04:24.061 --> 01:04:25.061
<i>Scott?</i>

01:04:25.095 --> 01:04:26.428
But you almost kissed.

01:04:26.463 --> 01:04:27.629
<i>Yeah, but we didn't.</i>

01:04:27.664 --> 01:04:29.731
Now he's talking
to perfect Alice,

01:04:29.766 --> 01:04:32.734
and they look happy
and... perfect,

01:04:32.769 --> 01:04:35.337
with their laughing
and their touching arms

01:04:35.372 --> 01:04:37.305
and their
perfectly-suited lives.

01:04:37.341 --> 01:04:39.007
Oh, I do not miss this part.

01:04:39.042 --> 01:04:41.142
I just keep thinking
about what William said,

01:04:41.178 --> 01:04:42.722
how no regular guy
would want to date me

01:04:42.746 --> 01:04:44.112
because I travel too much.

01:04:44.147 --> 01:04:46.214
That's not how I remember you
telling it.

01:04:46.250 --> 01:04:48.283
Especially a regular guy
with a kid.

01:04:48.352 --> 01:04:50.118
<i>Okay, look.
Focus.</i>

01:04:50.153 --> 01:04:52.254
Communication is key.

01:04:52.322 --> 01:04:54.890
Go to Scott and tell him
exactly how you're feeling,

01:04:54.958 --> 01:04:56.169
<i>and see
if he feels the same way.</i>

01:04:56.193 --> 01:04:57.292
What?

01:04:57.327 --> 01:04:58.627
Are you crazy?

01:04:58.662 --> 01:04:59.662
No one does that!

01:04:59.730 --> 01:05:01.062
Fine.
Then kiss him.

01:05:01.098 --> 01:05:01.863
You'll find out one way
or the other.

01:05:01.899 --> 01:05:03.064
Okay,

01:05:03.100 --> 01:05:06.201
so, uh,
rapture or mortification...

01:05:06.236 --> 01:05:07.202
These are my options?

01:05:07.237 --> 01:05:08.570
<i>Welcome to love.</i>

01:05:08.639 --> 01:05:10.038
<i>Now, I've got
to go feed my kids</i>

01:05:10.107 --> 01:05:11.973
<i>and communicate to my husband</i>

01:05:12.009 --> 01:05:13.887
that there's a limit
to how many college bowl games

01:05:13.911 --> 01:05:15.410
one person can watch in a day.

01:05:15.445 --> 01:05:16.445
Good luck.

01:05:16.480 --> 01:05:17.946
[Sighing]
Okay.

01:05:24.321 --> 01:05:25.287
[Scott]:
We're gonna be okay.

01:05:25.322 --> 01:05:26.588
[Marilyn]:
Oh, well,

01:05:26.623 --> 01:05:27.934
you did spend a lot of time
with her this week.

01:05:27.958 --> 01:05:29.002
I think we've always
known where we stand,

01:05:29.026 --> 01:05:30.091
though.

01:05:30.127 --> 01:05:32.227
[Marilyn]: Mm.
She is lovely, though.

01:05:32.262 --> 01:05:33.228
[Scott]: She is.

01:05:33.263 --> 01:05:35.597
No, she's great.

01:05:35.666 --> 01:05:36.598
She's really great,
you know.

01:05:36.667 --> 01:05:39.034
We've had some
fun moments,

01:05:39.069 --> 01:05:40.669
but I just don't
think she's it.

01:05:40.704 --> 01:05:42.015
[Marilyn]: Well,
I'm glad you figured that out

01:05:42.039 --> 01:05:44.606
before anything happened.

01:05:44.641 --> 01:05:45.785
Yeah, that would've
been awkward.

01:05:45.809 --> 01:05:48.443
Mm-hmm.

01:05:48.478 --> 01:05:51.079
You and Emory, however...

01:05:59.489 --> 01:06:00.889
You okay, Emory?

01:06:00.924 --> 01:06:02.924
Actually,
I'm not feeling too well.

01:06:02.960 --> 01:06:04.526
Um...

01:06:04.561 --> 01:06:06.328
Do you know if there's a cab
around?

01:06:06.363 --> 01:06:08.029
I don't want
to bug Scott or Marilyn.

01:06:08.065 --> 01:06:09.397
I can take you home.

01:06:09.466 --> 01:06:10.632
Thank you, Hal.

01:06:10.667 --> 01:06:12.467
Come on.

01:06:12.502 --> 01:06:14.803
I thought
I would never feel this again.

01:06:14.838 --> 01:06:15.603
You do?

01:06:15.639 --> 01:06:16.639
Yeah?

01:06:16.707 --> 01:06:17.572
You do?
You do.

01:06:17.607 --> 01:06:18.607
Yes!

01:06:20.243 --> 01:06:22.677
Mom, you don't...

01:06:22.713 --> 01:06:24.713
You don't think
being drawn to someone else

01:06:24.748 --> 01:06:25.647
is a betrayal?

01:06:25.682 --> 01:06:26.948
No.

01:06:26.984 --> 01:06:28.283
No, I don't.

01:06:28.318 --> 01:06:30.063
I think it's the most
natural thing in the world,

01:06:30.087 --> 01:06:31.953
if it's the right person.

01:06:33.457 --> 01:06:34.522
Is she?

01:06:34.558 --> 01:06:35.757
Oh...

01:06:35.792 --> 01:06:36.792
She might be.

01:06:38.328 --> 01:06:40.729
Then don't wait, Scott.

01:06:40.797 --> 01:06:42.831
Never, ever postpone
the chance for joy

01:06:42.866 --> 01:06:44.599
if you get it,
all right?

01:06:44.634 --> 01:06:46.968
Promise me.

01:06:47.004 --> 01:06:49.137
I promise...

01:06:49.206 --> 01:06:52.574
But that goes
for you, too, okay?

01:06:52.609 --> 01:06:55.477
You've spent a lot of your time
taking care of me and Katy.

01:06:55.512 --> 01:06:57.979
Yes, because
I've been worried about you.

01:06:58.015 --> 01:06:59.495
Well, you don't have
to worry anymore.

01:07:02.152 --> 01:07:03.651
No.

01:07:03.687 --> 01:07:06.087
No, I don't, do I?
I don't.

01:07:07.691 --> 01:07:09.090
I love you.

01:07:10.394 --> 01:07:11.826
I love you, too.

01:07:11.862 --> 01:07:13.428
Yeah.

01:07:19.403 --> 01:07:21.269
- [Scott]: After you.
- [Marilyn]: Thank you.

01:07:21.338 --> 01:07:22.670
[Katy]: After you.

01:07:22.706 --> 01:07:23.571
[Marilyn]: Go on, honey.
Let's go.

01:07:23.640 --> 01:07:25.006
[Scott]: All right, ladies.

01:07:25.042 --> 01:07:26.085
[Marilyn]: Good night,
sweetheart. Love you.

01:07:26.109 --> 01:07:27.253
[Scott]:
Good night, good night,

01:07:27.277 --> 01:07:28.343
good night, good night.

01:07:28.378 --> 01:07:30.278
[Marilyn]: Say good night.

01:07:30.313 --> 01:07:32.473
- [Scott]: Good night.
- [Marilyn]: Let's go, let's go.

01:07:37.087 --> 01:07:41.856
[♪♪♪]

01:08:12.456 --> 01:08:14.622
[Scott]: Well done.

01:08:14.658 --> 01:08:15.890
Thank you.

01:08:15.926 --> 01:08:17.192
There you are.

01:08:17.227 --> 01:08:18.671
Hal said that you weren't
feeling well last night,

01:08:18.694 --> 01:08:19.975
and you had to leave
a bit early.

01:08:20.831 --> 01:08:22.363
Ah, sleep helped.
I'm fine.

01:08:22.399 --> 01:08:23.665
Good.

01:08:23.700 --> 01:08:26.000
Well, my famous pancakes
are almost ready.

01:08:27.170 --> 01:08:28.170
Where are you going?

01:08:29.272 --> 01:08:30.272
Home.

01:08:31.608 --> 01:08:32.774
Wait... what?

01:08:32.843 --> 01:08:33.908
Yeah, my
editor called,

01:08:33.944 --> 01:08:35.020
and I got a new assignment.

01:08:35.045 --> 01:08:36.389
I've got to go to Katmandu
tomorrow.

01:08:36.412 --> 01:08:38.179
But, I mean...
Tomorrow's Christmas day.

01:08:38.215 --> 01:08:39.447
I know, that's...

01:08:39.483 --> 01:08:41.182
That's the way
it goes sometimes.

01:08:41.251 --> 01:08:43.651
But we still haven't
gone sledding,

01:08:43.687 --> 01:08:45.220
or watched Christmas movies.

01:08:45.255 --> 01:08:47.020
I know, sweetie, I'm sorry.
I really...

01:08:47.057 --> 01:08:48.777
I wish we could have done
those things, too.

01:08:54.029 --> 01:08:55.029
Emory's leaving!

01:08:55.098 --> 01:08:57.298
What?
It's Christmas Eve.

01:08:57.334 --> 01:08:58.978
[Scott]: So you can't leave
a little bit later?

01:08:59.002 --> 01:09:01.102
Like, after Christmas?

01:09:01.138 --> 01:09:02.970
I'm afraid not.
I...

01:09:03.038 --> 01:09:04.317
Plus, there's this storm
coming in,

01:09:04.341 --> 01:09:05.773
so I should probably head out

01:09:05.841 --> 01:09:08.542
before I get...
Stuck again.

01:09:10.779 --> 01:09:12.913
It was so nice to meet you!

01:09:12.948 --> 01:09:15.416
Oh, you, too, Emory.

01:09:17.888 --> 01:09:20.020
And you, little one...

01:09:20.055 --> 01:09:22.991
You have been
one of the best parts

01:09:23.026 --> 01:09:24.666
of this whole Christmas
getaway adventure.

01:09:24.694 --> 01:09:26.661
[Katy]:
I wish you could stay longer.

01:09:31.134 --> 01:09:33.067
All right,
I'd better go.

01:09:43.979 --> 01:09:45.546
Emory, wait.

01:09:47.317 --> 01:09:48.317
Hey.

01:09:50.020 --> 01:09:52.220
Why do I feel like there's
something more going on here?

01:09:53.622 --> 01:09:55.223
I'm really sorry
to disappoint Katy.

01:09:55.292 --> 01:09:57.292
Then don't.

01:09:57.327 --> 01:09:58.327
Stay.

01:10:00.730 --> 01:10:03.064
Merry Christmas, Scott.

01:10:27.524 --> 01:10:29.624
What happened?

01:10:29.659 --> 01:10:31.593
I have no idea.

01:11:08.365 --> 01:11:09.530
Hey, uh,

01:11:09.566 --> 01:11:12.667
your rear tire's
a little flat.

01:11:12.702 --> 01:11:14.435
Really?

01:11:16.239 --> 01:11:18.873
[Veronica, on phone]:
<i>Okay, calm down.</i>

01:11:18.908 --> 01:11:21.042
I am calm.

01:11:21.077 --> 01:11:23.711
Crushed, embarrassed,
and heartsick, but calm.

01:11:23.747 --> 01:11:25.380
Why are you embarrassed?

01:11:25.448 --> 01:11:26.881
Because
it's always embarrassing

01:11:26.950 --> 01:11:29.150
when you put yourself out there
for another person.

01:11:29.185 --> 01:11:30.151
<i>But you didn't.</i>

01:11:30.186 --> 01:11:31.252
Not really.

01:11:31.288 --> 01:11:32.320
That's not true.

01:11:32.389 --> 01:11:34.389
<i>No, you did
the whole subtextual</i>

01:11:34.424 --> 01:11:36.335
<i>"i-like-you-do-you-like-me?"
Thing with your eyes,</i>

01:11:36.359 --> 01:11:38.559
but you never actually
put yourself out there

01:11:38.595 --> 01:11:41.462
by telling him how you feel,
or kissing him.

01:11:41.498 --> 01:11:43.264
And it turns out,
that's a good thing

01:11:43.300 --> 01:11:45.600
because I now have
a tiny sliver of dignity

01:11:45.635 --> 01:11:48.136
onto which I'm now clinging,
thank you.

01:11:48.204 --> 01:11:49.548
Well,
if there's one positive thing

01:11:49.572 --> 01:11:50.838
that's come out of this,

01:11:50.874 --> 01:11:52.373
it's been your writing.

01:11:52.409 --> 01:11:53.541
Yeah.

01:11:55.512 --> 01:11:57.612
You know, I think
I'm going to take some time,

01:11:57.647 --> 01:11:58.647
try and work on the book.

01:11:58.682 --> 01:12:00.114
That's good news,

01:12:00.150 --> 01:12:02.317
especially
after this last article.

01:12:02.385 --> 01:12:03.318
You liked it?

01:12:03.386 --> 01:12:05.086
<i>I loved it.</i>

01:12:05.121 --> 01:12:07.255
You put more of yourself
into this one, by far.

01:12:08.391 --> 01:12:09.691
What do you mean?

01:12:09.726 --> 01:12:11.793
<i>Well, lately,
you've been traveling so much,</i>

01:12:11.828 --> 01:12:14.696
it's like you've developed
this detachment.

01:12:14.764 --> 01:12:15.797
Detachment?

01:12:15.832 --> 01:12:17.098
<i>Yeah, more and more,</i>

01:12:17.133 --> 01:12:18.733
especially
in your holiday articles

01:12:18.768 --> 01:12:20.301
where you write
about traditions...

01:12:20.370 --> 01:12:22.904
Almost like an anthropologist.

01:12:22.939 --> 01:12:24.172
I had no idea.

01:12:24.207 --> 01:12:25.239
<i>I know.</i>

01:12:25.308 --> 01:12:27.041
That's why I kind of fibbed

01:12:27.110 --> 01:12:29.243
about
the Phil Laskert situation.

01:12:29.279 --> 01:12:30.945
He didn't get stuck
on an ice floe again?

01:12:30.980 --> 01:12:32.213
No, he did,

01:12:32.248 --> 01:12:33.592
but he could've still written
the article.

01:12:33.616 --> 01:12:35.350
Then why did you ask me
to do it?

01:12:35.385 --> 01:12:38.186
Because as your friend
and your editor,

01:12:38.221 --> 01:12:40.688
I was hoping that if you had
a reason to get involved

01:12:40.724 --> 01:12:42.824
<i>in the kind of Christmas
you never had growing up,</i>

01:12:42.859 --> 01:12:45.426
<i>maybe you'd understand
what makes it so special,</i>

01:12:45.462 --> 01:12:47.729
and you might develop
a deeper connection to it.

01:12:51.568 --> 01:12:54.869
Well, that worked out better
than you could've hoped.

01:13:05.315 --> 01:13:07.582
Can I show you something?

01:13:09.219 --> 01:13:10.718
Sure.

01:13:10.754 --> 01:13:12.854
Always.
What do you got?

01:13:14.290 --> 01:13:15.957
It's my
Christmas present

01:13:15.992 --> 01:13:17.992
to you and Emory.

01:13:18.061 --> 01:13:20.261
I e-mailed it
to her, too.

01:13:20.296 --> 01:13:22.029
Just in time.

01:13:24.768 --> 01:13:26.134
All right.

01:13:32.342 --> 01:13:34.242
[♪♪♪]

01:13:39.015 --> 01:13:42.183
"Thank you for helping me
make the best Christmas.

01:13:42.218 --> 01:13:43.218
Katy."

01:13:44.988 --> 01:13:46.354
♪ Christmas ♪

01:13:46.423 --> 01:13:48.589
♪ The snow's coming down ♪

01:13:48.625 --> 01:13:50.124
♪ Christmas ♪

01:13:50.193 --> 01:13:52.427
♪ I'm watching it fall ♪

01:13:52.462 --> 01:13:53.928
♪ Christmas ♪

01:13:53.997 --> 01:13:56.197
♪ Lots of people around ♪

01:13:56.232 --> 01:13:57.732
♪ Christmas ♪

01:13:57.801 --> 01:14:00.201
♪ Baby, please come home ♪

01:14:00.270 --> 01:14:01.402
♪ Christmas ♪

01:14:01.438 --> 01:14:03.604
♪ The church bells in town ♪

01:14:03.640 --> 01:14:05.206
♪ Christmas ♪

01:14:05.241 --> 01:14:07.375
♪ Are ringing in song ♪

01:14:07.410 --> 01:14:08.910
♪ Christmas ♪

01:14:08.945 --> 01:14:11.078
♪ Full of happy sounds ♪

01:14:11.147 --> 01:14:12.613
♪ Christmas ♪

01:14:12.649 --> 01:14:15.283
♪ Baby, please come home ♪

01:14:15.318 --> 01:14:19.153
♪ They're singing
deck the halls ♪

01:14:19.222 --> 01:14:22.857
♪ But it's not like Christmas
at all ♪

01:14:22.892 --> 01:14:26.627
♪ 'Cause I remember
when you were here ♪

01:14:26.663 --> 01:14:29.864
♪ And all the fun
we had last year ♪

01:14:29.933 --> 01:14:31.199
♪ Christmas ♪

01:14:31.267 --> 01:14:33.434
♪ Pretty lights on the tree ♪

01:14:33.470 --> 01:14:35.036
♪ Christmas ♪

01:14:35.071 --> 01:14:37.238
♪ I'm watching them shine ♪

01:14:37.273 --> 01:14:38.873
♪ Christmas ♪

01:14:38.908 --> 01:14:40.875
♪ You should be here with me ♪

01:14:40.910 --> 01:14:42.577
♪ Christmas ♪

01:14:42.645 --> 01:14:44.946
♪ Baby, please come home ♪

01:14:50.587 --> 01:14:52.587
That was just beautiful,
Katy.

01:14:55.158 --> 01:14:56.158
Dad?

01:14:58.328 --> 01:15:00.361
I love it.

01:15:02.765 --> 01:15:04.265
[Emory]:
You were right.

01:15:04.300 --> 01:15:05.900
Emory?
I can barely hear you.

01:15:05.935 --> 01:15:08.002
[Audio breaking up]
<i>I said you were right.</i>

01:15:08.037 --> 01:15:10.004
<i>I never really put
myself out there.</i>

01:15:10.039 --> 01:15:11.506
I never told him
how I felt.

01:15:11.541 --> 01:15:13.074
I just bolted.

01:15:13.142 --> 01:15:14.954
<i>Honey, I think you're saying
really important things,</i>

01:15:14.978 --> 01:15:17.512
especially the part
about me being right,

01:15:17.580 --> 01:15:18.657
<i>but the reception is awful.</i>

01:15:18.681 --> 01:15:19.681
Oh, no!

01:15:19.716 --> 01:15:22.216
[Tires squealing]

01:15:22.252 --> 01:15:23.584
[Engine dying]

01:15:25.688 --> 01:15:27.522
Veronica?

01:15:27.557 --> 01:15:28.823
Veronica, can you hear me?

01:15:28.858 --> 01:15:30.458
[Engine spluttering]

01:15:32.896 --> 01:15:34.395
[Engine dying]

01:15:34.430 --> 01:15:37.598
I'm on a road
just outside pine grove.

01:15:37.634 --> 01:15:40.034
Emory? Emory!

01:15:41.671 --> 01:15:43.070
Veronica?

01:16:03.993 --> 01:16:06.060
Okay, you,
it's time for bed.

01:16:06.095 --> 01:16:08.062
Very busy day
tomorrow.

01:16:08.097 --> 01:16:09.097
Okay.

01:16:09.165 --> 01:16:10.898
Okay.
Love you.

01:16:14.037 --> 01:16:15.002
Mwah!

01:16:15.038 --> 01:16:15.970
Good night.

01:16:16.005 --> 01:16:17.605
Good night.

01:16:17.640 --> 01:16:19.473
Aw...

01:16:19.509 --> 01:16:20.708
[Cell phone ringing]

01:16:25.982 --> 01:16:26.747
Hey, Hal.
What's up?

01:16:26.816 --> 01:16:28.549
<i>Emory's car broke down.</i>

01:16:28.585 --> 01:16:29.995
<i>Her friend, Veronica,
just called me.</i>

01:16:30.019 --> 01:16:32.320
<i>Did she say where Emory was?</i>

01:16:32.355 --> 01:16:34.488
<i>No, her phone cut out.</i>

01:16:34.557 --> 01:16:36.958
Okay, I'll check the direction
that I saw her drive out.

01:16:37.026 --> 01:16:37.892
Uh, stay in touch.

01:16:37.927 --> 01:16:39.260
What?

01:16:39.295 --> 01:16:41.262
Emory's car broke down.

01:16:41.331 --> 01:16:42.708
She's somewhere
on the side of the road, so...

01:16:42.732 --> 01:16:43.732
Be careful!

01:16:55.244 --> 01:16:56.410
Whoo...

01:17:06.289 --> 01:17:07.655
[Shivering]

01:17:14.831 --> 01:17:17.131
[Chuckling]

01:17:17.166 --> 01:17:19.033
Merry Christmas.

01:17:21.938 --> 01:17:23.838
[Engine humming]

01:17:25.141 --> 01:17:27.108
[Knocking]

01:17:30.680 --> 01:17:32.713
You've really got to think
about getting a new car.

01:17:34.150 --> 01:17:35.583
- You think?
- Come on.

01:17:40.023 --> 01:17:41.856
How did you know?

01:17:41.891 --> 01:17:44.425
Your friend called Hal,
and Hal called me,

01:17:44.460 --> 01:17:45.926
and I came looking.

01:17:45.962 --> 01:17:47.728
Well, thank you.

01:17:47.764 --> 01:17:49.597
We're not in the clear yet.

01:17:49.632 --> 01:17:51.532
I mean...
This visibility's dangerous.

01:17:51.567 --> 01:17:52.567
I almost turned back.

01:17:54.070 --> 01:17:55.070
Why didn't you?

01:17:57.373 --> 01:17:59.006
I care about you.

01:18:03.279 --> 01:18:04.912
You know,
until we can see clearly again,

01:18:04.947 --> 01:18:05.713
we're going to have
to wait this out here,

01:18:05.748 --> 01:18:08.516
so it looks like

01:18:08.551 --> 01:18:10.151
you're stuck with me
a little longer.

01:18:10.186 --> 01:18:11.552
I'm sorry about all this.

01:18:11.621 --> 01:18:13.921
I know it isn't exactly
part of your Christmas plans.

01:18:19.796 --> 01:18:21.195
I just...

01:18:21.230 --> 01:18:22.730
I just, I don't know
why you left.

01:18:22.765 --> 01:18:24.365
I told you,

01:18:24.400 --> 01:18:25.711
my editor gave me
a new assignment.

01:18:25.735 --> 01:18:27.301
C'mon, Emory.

01:18:27.336 --> 01:18:28.903
Something happened.

01:18:28.971 --> 01:18:30.204
Just be honest with me.

01:18:30.273 --> 01:18:32.840
Tell me, why
did you leave?

01:18:32.909 --> 01:18:34.642
I was trying
to make it easier for you.

01:18:36.612 --> 01:18:37.778
Easier?

01:18:37.814 --> 01:18:43.217
I heard you talking to Marilyn
about me...

01:18:43.252 --> 01:18:44.652
How we're not suited
for each other.

01:18:46.222 --> 01:18:47.254
So I decided

01:18:47.290 --> 01:18:50.124
to get out of dodge,
so to speak.

01:18:50.159 --> 01:18:52.426
I said that about Alice...

01:18:54.397 --> 01:18:56.697
Whom, let
the record show,

01:18:56.733 --> 01:18:59.567
I have
zero romantic interest in.

01:19:01.838 --> 01:19:02.803
But she's perfect.

01:19:02.839 --> 01:19:04.238
Not for me.

01:19:07.076 --> 01:19:08.187
You know, I happened to notice

01:19:08.211 --> 01:19:11.579
that your car is facing north,

01:19:11.614 --> 01:19:13.080
instead of south.

01:19:15.118 --> 01:19:17.685
I was headed back
to the cabin.

01:19:19.455 --> 01:19:22.089
I got the email from Katy,
with the photos.

01:19:22.125 --> 01:19:23.791
I saw it, too.

01:19:23.860 --> 01:19:24.892
I tried
to convince myself

01:19:24.927 --> 01:19:27.061
that what I was feeling
wasn't true.

01:19:28.731 --> 01:19:31.132
But then she captured it.

01:19:31.167 --> 01:19:32.967
Yeah.

01:19:33.002 --> 01:19:34.802
She did.

01:19:39.275 --> 01:19:41.208
Let me be perfectly clear
with you.

01:19:41.244 --> 01:19:45.079
You captured all
of my attention

01:19:45.114 --> 01:19:48.115
from the moment
you threatened me

01:19:48.151 --> 01:19:50.417
with krav maga.

01:19:50.453 --> 01:19:53.320
That's what you get
for crashing my vacation.

01:19:53.389 --> 01:19:55.189
You crashed mine.

01:19:57.493 --> 01:19:59.994
Scott, I've never felt this way
about anyone before.

01:20:01.197 --> 01:20:03.497
It feels right.

01:20:05.835 --> 01:20:07.334
So we're in this together?

01:20:07.403 --> 01:20:09.637
All the way.

01:20:13.476 --> 01:20:15.042
[Car engine approaching]

01:20:15.077 --> 01:20:16.077
[Horn honking]

01:20:18.848 --> 01:20:20.247
Seriously?

01:20:29.826 --> 01:20:30.826
[Knocking]

01:20:36.833 --> 01:20:37.998
I'm no Rudolph,

01:20:38.034 --> 01:20:39.233
but I'll guide you
back home.

01:20:39.268 --> 01:20:40.601
Thanks, Hal.

01:20:43.840 --> 01:20:45.906
[Laughing]

01:20:48.344 --> 01:20:50.144
What?

01:20:50.179 --> 01:20:51.245
I'm just happy!

01:20:51.280 --> 01:20:52.280
[Laughing]

01:20:59.255 --> 01:21:00.821
Hey, why aren't
you in bed?

01:21:00.857 --> 01:21:02.289
I'm waiting for Santa.

01:21:04.861 --> 01:21:06.961
Oh, thank goodness.

01:21:06.996 --> 01:21:08.095
Oh, honey.

01:21:08.130 --> 01:21:09.230
Emory!

01:21:09.265 --> 01:21:10.631
You came back!

01:21:10.700 --> 01:21:12.166
Well, rumor has it

01:21:12.201 --> 01:21:14.235
the best Christmas ever
is happening here,

01:21:14.303 --> 01:21:15.536
so how could I miss that?

01:21:15.571 --> 01:21:16.503
You couldn't.

01:21:16.539 --> 01:21:17.705
Nope.

01:21:19.175 --> 01:21:20.608
Wouldn't miss it
for the world.

01:21:23.546 --> 01:21:24.546
[Laughing]

01:21:29.151 --> 01:21:30.484
It's called risgrynsgrot.

01:21:30.519 --> 01:21:31.852
Is this the
Swedish tradition

01:21:31.888 --> 01:21:33.153
with the almond?

01:21:33.189 --> 01:21:34.688
You know it?

01:21:34.757 --> 01:21:36.290
I travel a lot
with my mother.

01:21:36.325 --> 01:21:37.536
In fact, you'll meet her. She's
coming on the April cruise!

01:21:37.560 --> 01:21:38.826
Oh!

01:21:38.895 --> 01:21:39.760
Wait, you're going?

01:21:39.795 --> 01:21:40.795
I am.

01:21:42.431 --> 01:21:43.697
[Laughing]

01:21:45.034 --> 01:21:46.634
Okay, now, what...

01:21:46.669 --> 01:21:48.369
What exactly is this
tradition all about?

01:21:48.437 --> 01:21:51.839
Whoever finds the almond
will be married within a year.

01:21:51.908 --> 01:21:53.007
You are exempt,
little lady.

01:21:53.075 --> 01:21:54.942
[Laughing]

01:21:54.977 --> 01:21:58.112
I have all sorts of ideas
for the travel group.

01:21:58.180 --> 01:21:59.480
You know, Costa Rica

01:21:59.515 --> 01:22:01.482
is the most bio-diverse
place on the planet.

